public static $stressCards = array(
    array('Type'=>'Indifference', 'Description'=>'Sometimes a Character will become so detached and disinterested, that it impacts their ability to feel or care even slightly. In some cases this indifference is nothing more than a brief apathy, a limited lack of drive or moral guidance that will soon pass, but for others this coldness may be a lasting problem.', 'Rules'=>'Character must discard all Diamonds (<span class="t13ne-redcard">&diams;</span>) suited cards from Ordeal Pool, Style Reserves and Wyrd Tarot Hand, this continues with automatic Discarding of all Diamonds until they have zero Stress, Strain and Shock, when the Indifference Effect will end. Each Diamond (<span class="t13ne-redcard">&diams;</span>) Card Discarded removes Pips Stress or 1 Shock or 1 Strain from a Character or Descendant.'),  //ace - ambition
    array('Type'=>'Worries', 'Description'=>'Worries make a Character think about their issues, dwelling on what questions or issues are stressing them out. Time and time again their mind will return to their ','Rules'=>'Character may reduce their Stress, Strain, or Shock by 1 for each statement they make, that relates to their worries. Additionally they may reduce their Stress by spending Diamond Pips equal to the Stress on pacing back and forth, or they may pay Chi equal to their current Stress to remove a point of Shock, Strain or Stress.'),  //2 - wraith
    array('Type'=>'Working','Description'=>'You can always work through Stress. Sometimes you can just put your head down and get on with things, and when you lift your head something has changed. Sometimes this time is best spent working a physically demanding job, or one that keeps your mind occupied, other times the best way to work through it is a nap.', 'Rules'=>'A Character may remove 1 point of Stress, Strain or Shock by working on, or working at ignoring, their problems for twenty-minutes.'),  //3 - grindstone
    array('Type'=>'Escapism','Description'=>'Characters who use escapism avoid their Stress by throwing themselves into something else. This might be a fictional universe, a fantasy, a paranoid world view, or escape an old relationship for a new love or change job.', 'Rules'=>'Escapism Characters create a new Emotional, Inept, Bias, Mild, Duty or Devotion Quirk with a Bane of 1. Characters may move Stress into this new Hitch, increasing the Banes by 1 costs the current Banes in Stress.'),  //4 - book
    array('Type'=>'Complicated','Description'=>'Stress can interfere with your life, making it more complicated in every way. Self-sabotage can play a part too, stress acts against our better judgement and instincts at times, interfering in what we do.', 'Rules'=>'All Actions in the suited Facets (Awe, Craft, Orthodox, Quiet, Virtue, Zeal) add a Difficulty equal to the Character’s current Stress in Tao Sway / Score. If any penalised Action Succeeds it will reduce the Character’s Stress, Strain or Shock by 1 for each Success Level created.'),  //5 - forest
    array('Type'=>'Faith','Description'=>'Stress and its results can do odd things to a person. Sometimes it can drive them wild, other times it can "save" them, driving them into the loving arms of religion. Usually this will be a new religion for the Character, perhaps a new church or pastor if their old religion, but something about what they are selling the Character really seems to be buying. This can represent a spiritual awakening, or a vulnerable sort being preyed on by a cult.', 'Rules'=>'Characters are offered a choice. They may take a new Hitch (Emotional, Inept, Bias, Mild, Duty or Devotion) with Banes equal to the the Character’s current Stress, or they may increase another Hitch by 1 Bane for Stress equal to the current Hitch Banes, or they may discard parts of their Character such as Proficiencies, Descendants, Allies or even Annexes which will negate Stress equal to the Cost of the lost part in Chi.'),  //6 - sun
    array('Type'=>'Hardship','Description'=>'Stress makes things harder. Things that we could previously bear with grace become impossible to cope with, and all too often the Stress interferes with our skills and talents. Stress can even make us revel in these hardships, justifying and internalising the failures.', 'Rules'=>'All Diamond suited Actions (Awe, Craft, Orthodox, Quiet, Virtue, Zeal) add Difficulty equal to the Character’s current Stress in Intrepid Facet Sway. If a penalised Action fails the Character may reduce Stress or Strain by 1 per Success Level.'),  //7 - drive
    array('Type'=>'Struggling','Description'=>'Characters deep in Stress can struggle to cope. It can feel like they are drowning, unable to catch a breath between the wild buffets of fate. If they were less stressed they would cope, but it seems like everything is more difficult for these Characters now. Somehow though they will often struggle through, barely making ends meet until the stress lifts.', 'Rules'=>'Diamond Suited Facet Actions (Awe, Craft, Orthodox, Quiet, Virtue, Zeal) add Difficulty equal to the current Stress in Chi, all other Facet Actions add Difficulty equal to the current Stress as Tao Sway. If a penalised Action is a Stalemate then the Character may reduce Stress, Strain and Shock by 1.'), //8 - cultist
    array('Type'=>'Health','Description'=>'Stress, especially high stress over time, can have a very deleterious effect upon a Character’s health. Commonly a weakened immune system takes longer to shrug off infections and heal, and the Character may find themselves run down and exhausted from minor illnesses that would not normally affect them so much.', 'Rules'=>'Healing times for all Diamond Suited Wounds add the Current Stress as a Chi Extend Duration, even a Distract Wound can take a while to shake off when you are Stressed. Additionally all Diamond Suited Wounds that the Character takes will add current Stress to their Pips, including the Difficulty to treat and Stabilise (increasing the chances of Wounds Festering).'),  //9 - priest
     array('Type'=>'Disturbed','Description'=>'High Stress for hours, days, weeks or perhaps even years can profoundly alter a Character. Some people freak out if their schedule is disturbed even slightly, others need their sleep cycle disturbed before it becomes a problem. Others find themselves physically or emotionally disturbed. But this all amounts to the same thing.', 'Rules'=>'A Character who has become disturbed (by the latest Stressor) cannot rest or settle while this latest stressor continues. If they can find a way to cease the disturbance they will relieve all current Stress (but not Strain or Shock) and cease being disturbed, but until that time they will add their current Stress and the Tension-Level as a Chi Difficulty to all Actions that are not based on ceasing the disturbance (or at least getting far away). Even Actions that act to cease the disturbance will add the Character’s current Stress in Chi as additional Difficulty.'),  //10 - loner
    array('Type'=>'Phantoms','Description'=>'Stress can have profound effects on the mind, causing one to see and hear all sorts of things that are not happening. Memories, waking dreams, and stress can easily combine to create Phantom Characters, hallucinations who take on the appearance of people from the Character’s past.', 'Rules'=>'The Character’s current Stress and the current Tension Level are added together to create an amount of Chi. This Chi must be paid by the Character and is used to either purchase a "Phantom" version of a Character or create an entirely new "Phantom". The Phantom may haunt the Character, accusing them, often seemingly feeding on the Character’s own guilt and continues for a period of time equal to the Current Stress as Intrepid Facet Sway after which the phantom will vanish relieving Stress equal to the current Tension Level. Typically the Phantom will reappear anytime the Character’s current Stress plus the Tension Level is high enough to create them again. Phantoms are typically an extension of the Character, even if they do appear as ghosts, grey aliens, faeries, or shadow people, so trying to harm them with magic, for example, will usually harm the Character experiencing the Phantoms, of course sometimes Increated will use Phantoms as the basis of a Nightmare Form, in which case they can be targeted separately.'),  //J - teacher
    array('Type'=>'Monsters','Description'=>'Stress can make monsters of us all, but worse still Stress can make Monsters, not just mountains, out of molehills.', 'Rules'=>'The Character must pay Chi equal to the Character’s current Stress as Yarn. This Chi is used to purchase a new Character that can be a Force-of-Nature Extra with Monster Facets (Awe, Craft, Orthodox, Quiet, Virtue, Zeal). These "Monsters" may actually be physical issues such as natural disasters, or they may be aspects of the Character’s own Psyche, given hallucinatory or supernatural form. Then again they can be the Character themselves, unaware in their Stress-induced black-outs what they are doing. Other times the Character will project their problems on an actual Monster, tying their Arcs together. The only catharsis available to a Character here is to defeat, or at least survive the Monster, which will relieve Stress equal to the Monster Facet Boon.'),  //Q - forge
    array('Type'=>'Dangerous','Description'=>'Stress is dangerous, it can turn a simple mistake into a deadly danger, make a simple shock cause a heart attack, or make a Character hold a loaded gun to their own head.', 'Rules'=>'All Diamond (<span class="t13ne-redcard">&diams;</span>) Suited Ordeal cards that target the Character for an Attack add the Character’s current Stress as Yarn so 13 Stress adds 66 Pips to each card, but then relieves Stress equal to the original Card Pips, plus all Strains and Shocks. Unsuited cards add current Stress as Chi (13 Pips), but remove only the Pips Reduced, 1 Strain or 1 Shock.'),  //K - star
    //hearts PEHJLN Consuming, Vague, Doubt, Odd, Taboo, Scars
    array('Type'=>'Hardened', 'Description'=>'Sometimes a Character can become hardened, insensitive and incapable of caring. Hardboiled detectives, grizzled war veterans and the like, shrug off the ability to heal themselves and empathise, in favour of losing Stress.', 'Rules'=>'Character must discard all Hearts (<span class="t13ne-redcard">&hearts;</span>) cards from Ordeal Pool, Style Reserves and Wyrd Tarot Hand, until they have zero Stress. Each Heart Discarded removes Pips Stress, or 1 Strain or 1 Shock.'),   //ace - lovers
   array('Type'=>'Worries', 'Description'=>'Worries make a Character think about their issues, dwelling on what questions or issues are stressing them out.','Rules'=>'Character may reduce their Stress, Strain or Shock by 1 for each question they ask, or statement they make, that relates to their worries, or each Pip that they dedicate to "Healing Prayers", "Meditation" or similar Stress reduction techniques, or they may pay Chi equal to their current Stress to remove 1 Stress.'),  //2 -burnout
    array('Type'=>'Questioning','Description'=>'Asking the right questions at the right time can alleviate a lot of Stress for some people. Knowing what might be on the Test can make revision easier, for example.', 'Rules'=>'A Character may relieve Stress equal to the current Tension Level by asking any Character for advice about their problems.'),  //3 - question
    array('Type'=>'Coping','Description'=>'Coping mechanisms for stress vary from person to person. Some people drink, or take drugs (both illegal and medically prescribed), some throw themselves into religion, a hobby or work, and a few may cut or tattoo themselves. These coping mechanisms can grow rapidly becoming Flaws or even Woes as a Character relies on them to cope with Stress.', 'Rules'=>'Coping Characters create a new Vague, Consuming, Doubt, Odd, Taboo or Scars Quirk automatically initially with a Bane of 1. Characters may move Stress into this new Hitch, increasing the Banes by 1 relieves Stress equal to the current Hitch Banes.'),  //4 - myth
    array('Type'=>'Joking','Description'=>'Stress can make Characters feel tense and a natural way to relieve that tension and Stress is by making jokes, even if they are inappropriate to the situation at hand.', 'Rules'=>'Making a joke will relieve 1 Stress at any time, even if no one laughs because it is so inappropriate a joke or time.'),  //5 - joke
    array('Type'=>'Rebellion','Description'=>'Stress and its results can make a person feel like their life is spiralling out of their control, so they try to seize control again, often by an act of rebellion. This can result in all sorts of problems as parts of the Character’s life are damaged, discarded, lost, chased away, replaced, or forgotten.', 'Rules'=>'Characters who are rebelling are offered a choice. They may take a new Hitch (Consuming, Vague, Doubt, Odd, Taboo or Scars) with Banes equal to the the Character’s current Stress, or they may increase another Hitch by 1 Bane for Stress equal to the current Hitch Banes, or they may discard parts of their Character such as Proficiencies, Descendants, Allies or even Annexes which will relieve Stress equal to the Cost of the lost part in Chi'),  //6 - unicorn
    array('Type'=>'Hardships','Description'=>'Stress makes things harder. Things that we could previously bear with grace become impossible to cope with, and all too often the Stress interferes with our skills and talents. Stress can even make us revel in these hardships, justifying and internalising the failures.', 'Rules'=>'All Heart suited Actions (Enigma, Heresy, Jeer, Liberty, Phoenix, and Nature) add Difficulty equal to the Character’s current Stress in Intrepid Facet Sway. If a penalised Action fails the Character may reduce Stress, Strain or Shock by 1 for each Success Level achieved.'),  //7 - stag
    array('Type'=>'Struggling','Description'=>'Characters deep in Stress can struggle to cope. It can feel like they are drowning, unable to catch a breath between the wild buffets of fate. If they were less stressed they would cope, but it seems like everything is more difficult for these Characters now. Somehow though they will often struggle through, barely making ends meet until the stress lifts.', 'Rules'=>'Hearts Suited Facet Actions (Enigma, Heresy, Jeer, Liberty, Phoenix, and Nature) add Difficulty equal to the current Stress in Chi, unsuited Facet Actions add Difficulty equal to the current Stress as Tao Sway. If a penalised Action is a Stalemate then the Character may reduce Stress, Strain and Shock by 1.'),  //8 - wizard
    array('Type'=>'Health','Description'=>'Stress, especially high stress over time, can have a very deleterious effect upon a Character’s health. Commonly a weakened immune system takes longer to shrug off infections and heal, and the Character may find themselves run down and exhausted from minor illnesses that would not normally affect them so much.', 'Rules'=>'Healing times for all Heart Suited Wounds adds the Current Stress as a Chi Extend Duration, even a Distract Wound can take a while to shake off when you are Stressed. Additionally all Hearts Suited Wounds that the Character takes will add Current Stress to their Pips, including the Difficulty to treat and Stabilise (increasing the chances of Wounds Festering).'),  //9 lady
     array('Type'=>'Disturbed','Description'=>'High Stress for hours, days, weeks or perhaps even years can profoundly alter a Character. Some people freak out if their schedule is disturbed even slightly, others need their sleep cycle disturbed before it becomes a problem. Others find themselves physically or emotionally disturbed. But this all amounts to the same thing.', 'Rules'=>'A Character who has become disturbed (by the latest Stressor) cannot rest or settle while this latest stressor continues. If they can find a way to cease the disturbance they will relieve all current Stress and cease being disturbed, but until that time they will add their current Stress and the Tension-Level as a Chi Difficulty to all Actions that are not based on ceasing the disturbance (or at least getting far away). Even Actions that act to cease the disturbance will add the Character’s current Stress in Chi as additional Difficulty.'),  //10 - jester
    array('Type'=>'Delirium','Description'=>'Stress can have profound effects on the mind, causing one to see and hear all sorts of things that are not happening. Simply missing too much sleep can cause a healthy mind to micro-sleep and confuse the Character’s real and dream lives, and for some minds the confusion is more easily started, unusual brain chemistry and even normal development can lead to all manner of hallucinatory voices and imaginary friends knocking about the place.', 'Rules'=>'The Character’s current Stress and the current Tension Level are added together to create an amount of Chi. This Chi must be paid by the Character to side-step the Character partially into a Psycho-social "dream-space" or "metaphorical representation" that they will explore, encountering aspects of their own Character, and perhaps their mental image of close friends as metaphors and hallucinatory Extras. The Delirium continues for a period of time equal to the Current Stress as Intrepid Facet Sway after which the delirium will fade away removing Stress equal to the current Tension Level. Typically the Delirium will reappear anytime the Character’s current Stress plus the Tension Level is high enough to side-step them that far again. Deliriums are typically an extension of the Character, even if they do appear as faery forests, cloud castles, creepy dungeons or alien vistas, so trying to harm them, or the character’s within with magic, for example, will usually harm the Character experiencing the delirium.'),  //J - mask
   array('Type'=>'Monsters','Description'=>'Stress can make monsters of us all, but worse still Stress can make Monsters, not just mountains, out of molehills.', 'Rules'=>'The Character must pay Chi equal to the Character’s current Stress as Yarn. This Chi is used to purchase a new Character that can be a Force-of-Nature Extra with Monster Facets (Enigma, Heresy, Jeer, Liberty, Phoenix, and Nature). These "Monsters" may actually be physical issues such as natural disasters, or they may be aspects of the Characters own Psyche, given hallucinatory or supernatural form. Then again they can be the Character themselves, unaware in their Stress induced black-outs what they are doing. Other times the Character will project their problems on an actual Monster, tying their Arcs together. The only catharsis available to a Character here is to defeat, or at least survive the Monster, which will relieve Stress equal to the Monster Facet Boon.'),  //Q - cloak
    array('Type'=>'Dangerous','Description'=>'Stress is dangerous, it can turn a simple mistake into a deadly danger, make a simple shock cause a heart attack, or make a Character hold a loaded gun to their own head.', 'Rules'=>'All Hearts (<span class="t13ne-redcard">&hearts;</span>) Suited Ordeal cards that target the Character for an Attack add the Character’s current Stress as Yarn so 13 Stress adds 66 Pips to each card, but then relieves Stress equal to the original Card Pips, plus all Strains and Shocks. Unsuited cards add current Stress as Chi (13 Pips), but remove only the Pips Reduced, 1 Strain or 1 Shock.'),  //K - physician
    //clubs BDFRSW Lacking, Harrow, Unstable, Defensive, Desires, Doomed
    array('Type'=>'Sanctioned', 'Description'=>'Sometimes a Character can be told they must cease and desist some activity by lawyers, or a Character may finally let down their guard, or they may be captured and rather than being chained or imprisoned are kept under guard.', 'Rules'=>'Character must discard all Clubs (<span class="t13ne-blackcard">&clubs;</span>) cards from Ordeal Pool, Style Reserves and Wyrd Tarot Hand, until they have zero Stress. Each Club Discarded removes 1 Stress, 1 Strain, or 1 Shock.'),   //ace - court
    array('Type'=>'Worries', 'Description'=>'Worries make a Character think about their issues, dwelling on what questions or issues are stressing them out.','Rules'=>'Character may reduce their Stress by 1 for each statement that relates to their worries that they make, or each Clubs Pip Played on Psycho-social Actions that relate to their worries, or they may pay Chi equal to their current Stress to remove 1 Stress, 1 Strain or 1 Shock.'),  //2 -Eelafin
    array('Type'=>'Avoiding','Description'=>'You can always avoid Stress, sometimes if you are being stressed by a task you can just get it done, better yet, sometimes you can tell someone else to do it, and go and do something else.', 'Rules'=>'A Character may remove 1 point of Stress by ordering or paying another Character to help them with what ever is stressing them.'),  //3 - serpent
    array('Type'=>'Coping','Description'=>'Coping mechanisms for stress vary from person to person. Some people throw money away, chasing a new fling, others will pick a fight or become irritable, or defensive, a few may turn to magic with dubious repercussions. These coping mechanisms can grow rapidly becoming Flaws or even Woes as a Character relies on them to cope with Stress.', 'Rules'=>'Coping Characters create a new Lacking, Harrowed, Unstable, Defensive, Desires or Doomed Quirk automatically initially with a Bane of 1. Characters may move Stress into this Hitch, increasing the Banes by 1 for the current Banes in Stress any time the Hitch is Triggered.'),  //4 -waters
    array('Type'=>'Complicated','Description'=>'Stress can interfere with your life, making it more complicated in every way. Self-sabotage can play a part too, stress acts against our better judgement and instincts at times, interfering in what we do.', 'Rules'=>'All Actions in the suited Facets (Burden, Dominion, Fury, Rook, Sin, or Wyrd) add a Difficulty equal to the Character’s current Stress in Tao Sway. If a penalised Action Succeeds it will reduce the Character’s Stress by 1.'),  //5 - shield
    array('Type'=>'Lost','Description'=>'Stress and its results can make a person feel lost, directionless and adrift, and usually this leads a Character to wander away from their old life and worries and into new trouble. The thing to remember about trouble is that it can often be quite a lot of fun, at first...', 'Rules'=>'Characters who are spiralling are offered a choice. They may take a new Hitch (Lacking, Harrow, Unstable, Defensive, Desires, Doomed) with Banes equal to the the Character’s current Stress, or they may increase another Hitch by 1 Bane for Stress equal to the current Hitch Banes, or they may discard parts of their Character such as Proficiencies, Descendants, Allies or even Annexes which will negate Stress equal to the Cost of the lost part in Chi'),  //6 - horde
   array('Type'=>'Harder','Description'=>'Stress makes things harder. Things that we could previously bear with grace become impossible to cope with, and all too often the Stress interferes with our skills and talents. Stress can even make us revel in these hardships, justifying and internalising the failures.', 'Rules'=>'All Club suited Actions (Burden, Dominion, Fury, Rook, Sin, or Wyrd) add Difficulty equal to the Character’s current Stress in Intrepid Facet Sway. If a penalised Action fails the Character may reduce Stress by 1.'),  //7 - crystal
    array('Type'=>'Struggling','Description'=>'Characters deep in Stress can struggle to cope. It can feel like they are drowning, unable to catch a breath between the wild buffets of fate. If they were less stressed they would cope, but it seems like everything is more difficult for these Characters now. Somehow though they will often struggle through, barely making ends meet until the stress lifts.', 'Rules'=>'Club Suited Facet Actions (Burden, Dominion, Fury, Rook, Sin, or Wyrd) add Difficulty equal to the current Stress in Chi, other Facet Actions add Difficulty equal to the current Stress as Tao Sway. If a penalised Action is a Stalemate then the Character may reduce Stress, Strain and Shock by 1.'),  //9 - scythe
    array('Type'=>'Health','Description'=>'Stress, especially high stress over time, can have a very deleterious effect upon a Character’s health. Commonly a weakened immune system takes longer to shrug off infections and heal, and the Character may find themselves run down and exhausted from minor illnesses that would not normally affect them so much.', 'Rules'=>'Healing times for all Clubs Suited Wounds adds the Current Stress as a Chi Extend Duration, even a Distract Wound can take a while to shake off when you are Stressed. Additionally all Club Suited Wounds that the Character takes will add Current Stress to their Pips, including the Difficulty to treat and Stabilise (increasing the chances of Wounds Festering).'),  //9 - crown
    array('Type'=>'Disturbed','Description'=>'High Stress for hours, days, weeks or perhaps even years can profoundly alter a Character. Some people freak out if their schedule is disturbed even slightly, others need their sleep cycle disturbed before it becomes a problem. Others find themselves physically or emotionally disturbed. But this all amounts to the same thing.', 'Rules'=>'A Character who has become disturbed (by the latest Stressor) cannot rest or settle while this latest stressor continues. If they can find a way to cease the disturbance they will relieve 10 Stress and cease being disturbed, but until that time they will add their current Stress and the Tension-Level as a Chi Difficulty to all Actions that are not based on ceasing the disturbance (or at least getting far away). Even Actions that act to cease the disturbance will add the Character’s current Stress in Chi as additional Difficulty.'),  //10 - guardian
    array('Type'=>'Nightmares','Description'=>'Stress can have profound effects on the mind, but real stress upsets the unconscious, making dreams become nightmares.', 'Rules'=>'The Character’s current Stress and the current Tension Level are added together to create an amount of Chi. This Chi must be paid by the Character to side-step the Character partially into a Psycho-social space where they work through their stress confronting a series of nightmare scenarios that the Stresses represent. The Nightmares continue for a period of time equal to the Current Stress as Chi when the Character sleeps after which the nightmare will cease relieving 1 Stress. Typically the nightmares will reappear anytime the Character’s current Stress plus the Tension Level is high enough to create them again. Nightmares are typically an extension of the Character, so trying to harm them with magic, for example, will usually harm the Character experiencing the nightmares, of course sometimes Increated will use nightmares as the basis of a Nightmare Form, in which case they can be targeted.'),  //J - tempest
    array('Type'=>'Monsters','Description'=>'Stress can make monsters of us all, but worse still Stress can make Monsters, not just mountains, out of molehills.', 'Rules'=>'The Character must pay Chi equal to the Character’s current Stress as Yarn. This Chi is used to purchase a new Character that can be a Force-of-Nature Extra with Monster Facets (Burden, Dominion, Fury, Rook, Sin, or Wyrd). These "Monsters" may actually be physical issues such as natural disasters, or they may be aspects of the Characters own Psyche, given hallucinatory or supernatural form. Then again they can be the Character themselves, unaware in their Stress induced black-outs what they are doing. Other times the Character will project their problems on an actual Monster, tying their Arcs together. The only catharsis available to a Character here is to defeat, or at least survive the Monster, which will relieve Stress up to Monster Facet Boon.'),  //Q - inn
    array('Type'=>'Dangerous','Description'=>'Stress is dangerous, it can turn a simple mistake into a deadly danger, make a simple shock cause a heart attack, or make a Character hold a loaded gun to their own head.', 'Rules'=>'All Clubs  (<span class="t13ne-blackcard">&clubs;</span>) Suited Ordeal cards that target the Character for an Attack add the Character’s current Stress as Yarn so 13 Stress adds 66 Pips to each card, but then relieves Stress equal to the original Card Pips, plus all Strains and Shocks. Unsuited cards add current Stress as Chi (13 Pips), but remove only the Pips Reduced, 1 Strain or 1 Shock.'),  //K - fae noble
    //spades GIKMTY Binding, Laments, Confined, Corrupted, Offensive, Loss of Sense
    array('Type'=>'Between', 'Description'=>'Sometimes a Character is neither one thing or the other, in neither one place or the other, and this can make it difficult for them to act', 'Rules'=>'Character must discard all Spades (<span class="t13ne-blackcard">&spades;</span>) cards from Ordeal Pool, Style Reserves and Wyrd Tarot Hand, until they have zero Stress. Each Spade Discarded removes 1 Stress.'),   //ace - threshold
    array('Type'=>'Worries', 'Description'=>'Worries make a Character think about their issues, dwelling on what questions or issues are stressing them out.','Rules'=>'Character may reduce their Stress by 1 for each statement they make, that relates to their worries, character that they talk to about it, or they may pay Chi equal to their current Stress as Tao Sway to remove 1 Stress.'), //2 -swamp
    array('Type'=>'Release','Description'=>'Sometimes a single event is enough to release some Stress. If it is the right event', 'Rules'=>'A Character may remove 1 point of Stress after a period of any unrelated activity equal to the Current Stress as Chi Extend Duration.'),  //3 - key
    array('Type'=>'Coping','Description'=>'Coping mechanisms for stress vary from person to person. Some people will talk about what is stressing them, creating a new narrative out of the situation at had, others will let stress get the better of them, corrupting them, or driving them to attack, others will hide themselves away, and very few may lose senses.  These coping mechanisms can grow rapidly becoming Flaws or even Woes as a Character relies on them to cope with Stress.', 'Rules'=>'Coping Characters create a new Binding, Laments, Confined, Corrupted, Offensive or Loss-of-Sense Quirk automatically initially with a Bane of 1. Characters may move Stress into this Hitch, increasing the Banes by 1 for the current Banes in Stress any time the Hitch is Triggered.'),  //4 - tower
    array('Type'=>'Complicated','Description'=>'Stress can interfere with your life, making it more complicated in every way. Self-sabotage can play a part too, stress acts against our better judgement and instincts at times, interfering in what we do.', 'Rules'=>'All Actions in the suited Facets (Gossamer, Inertia, Key, Miasma, Trial or Yonder) add a Difficulty equal to the Character’s current Stress in Tao Sway. If a penalised Action Succeeds it will reduce the Character’s Stress by 1.'),  //5 - sail
