    array('Type'=>'Hard-times','Description'=>'Stress makes things harder. Things that we could previously bear with grace become impossible to cope with, and all too often the Stress interferes with our skills and talents. Stress can even make us revel in these hardships, justifying and internalising the failures.', 'Rules'=>'All Spades suited Actions (Gossamer, Inertia, Key, Miasma, Trial or Yonder) add Difficulty equal to the Character’s current Stress in Intrepid Facet Sway. If a penalised Action fails the Character may reduce Stress by 1.'),  //7 - sword
    array('Type'=>'Struggling','Description'=>'Characters deep in Stress can struggle to cope. It can feel like they are drowning, unable to catch a breath between the wild buffets of fate. If they were less stressed they would cope, but it seems like everything is more difficult for these Characters now. Somehow though they will often struggle through, barely making ends meet until the stress lifts.', 'Rules'=>'Spades Suited Facet Actions (Gossamer, Inertia, Key, Miasma, Trial or Yonder) add Difficulty equal to the current Stress in Chi, all other Facet Actions add Difficulty equal to the current Stress as Tao Sway. If a penalised Action is a Stalemate then the Character may reduce Stress by 1.'),  //8 - rival
    array('Type'=>'Health','Description'=>'Stress, especially high stress over time, can have a very deleterious effect upon a Character’s health. Commonly a weakened immune system takes longer to shrug off infections and heal, and the Character may find themselves run down and exhausted from minor illnesses that would not normally affect them so much.', 'Rules'=>'Healing times for all Spades Suited Wounds adds the Current Stress as a Chi Extend Duration, even a Distract Wound can take a while to shake off when you are Stressed. Additionally all Spades Suited Wounds that the Character takes will add Current Stress to their Pips, including the Difficulty to treat and Stabilise (increasing the chances of Wounds Festering).'),//9 - robot
     array('Type'=>'Disturbed','Description'=>'High Stress for hours, days, weeks or perhaps even years can profoundly alter a Character. Some people freak out if their schedule is disturbed even slightly, others need their sleep cycle disturbed before it becomes a problem. Others find themselves physically or emotionally disturbed. But this all amounts to the same thing.', 'Rules'=>'A Character who has become disturbed (by the latest Stressor) cannot rest or settle while this latest stressor continues. If they can find a way to cease the disturbance they will relieve 10 Stress and cease being disturbed, but until that time they will add their current Stress and the Tension-Level as a Chi Difficulty to all Actions that are not based on ceasing the disturbance (or at least getting far away). Even Actions that act to cease the disturbance will add the Character’s current Stress in Chi as additional Difficulty.'),  //10 - lion
    array('Type'=>'Hallucinations','Description'=>'Stress can have profound effects on the mind, causing one to see and hear all sorts of things that are not happening. Simply missing too much sleep can cause a healthy mind to micro-sleep and confuse the Character’s real and dream lives, and for some minds the confusion is more easily started, unusual brain chemistry and even normal development can lead to all manner of hallucinatory voices and imaginary friends knocking about the place.', 'Rules'=>'The Character’s current Stress and the current Tension Level are added together to create an amount of Chi. This Chi must be paid by the Character  and is used to either purchase a new "Hallucinatory" Character or to side-step the Character partially into a Psycho-social dream space. The Hallucination continues  for a period of time equal to the Current Stress as Intrepid Facet Sway after which the hallucination will vanish removing 1 Stress. Typically the hallucination will reappear anytime the Character’s current Stress plus the Tension Level is high enough to create them again. Hallucinations are typically an extension of the Character, even if they do appear as grey aliens, faeries, ghosts or shadow people, so trying to harm them with magic, for example, will usually harm the Character experiencing the hallucinations, of course sometimes Increated will use hallucinations as the basis of a Nightmare Form, in which case they can be targeted.'),  //J - explorer
    array('Type'=>'Monsters','Description'=>'Stress can make monsters of us all, but worse still Stress can make Monsters, not just mountains, out of molehills.', 'Rules'=>'The Character must pay Chi equal to the Character’s current Stress as Yarn. This Chi is used to purchase a new Character that can be a Force-of-Nature Extra with Monster Facets (Gossamer, Inertia, Key, Miasma, Trial or Yonder). These "Monsters" may actually be physical issues such as natural disasters, or they may be aspects of the Characters own Psyche, given hallucinatory or supernatural form. Then again they can be the Character themselves, unaware in their Stress induced black-outs what they are doing. Other times the Character will project their problems on an actual Monster, tying their Arcs together. The only catharsis available to a Character here is to defeat, or at least survive the Monster, which will relieve up to 12 Stress.'), //Q -scope
    array('Type'=>'Dangerous','Description'=>'Stress is dangerous, it can turn a simple mistake into a deadly danger, make a simple shock cause a heart attack, or make a Character hold a loaded gun to their own head.', 'Rules'=>'All Spades (<span class="t13ne-blackcard">&spades;</span>) Suited Ordeal cards that target the Character for an Attack add the Character’s current Stress as Yarn so 13 Stress adds 66 Pips to each card, but then relieves Stress equal to the original Card Pips, plus all Strains and Shocks. Unsuited cards add current Stress as Chi (13 Pips), but remove only the Pips Reduced, 1 Strain or 1 Shock.'), //K- butcher
   array('Type'=>'Berserk','Description'=>'Stress can cause a Character to snap, becoming a furious engine of destruction. This creates a glorious moment of cathartic release, with the Character burning the Stress to augment their damage, as the Character attacks friend and foe alike, relieving huge amounts of Stress. However, the repercussions of this event may create more Stress than is lost.', 'Rules'=>'All Ordeal cards played that attack another Character or Descendant add current Stress as Chi to the Pips of the Attack and reduce the Stress by 1 until the Character has no Stress remaining. However, after the dust has settled the Character will gain Stress equal to highest Character or Descendant type (or the total Group Size whichever is higher) injured or destroyed in Chi. E.g. A Berserker that killed a Hero or almost 100 Extras and Grunts would add 12 Stress after the Berserk had finished.'), // world
    array('Type'=>'Narrative Incursion','Description'=>'Stress can break a Character, ruining their tales, derailing their arcs and upsetting Plots that have Embodied in them. Then again sometimes the Plots that are working behind the Scenes can decide to intervene and keep a Character on track, throwing some narrative event at the Character that forces them to confront their own faults and deal with their Stress.', 'Rules'=>'The Character immediately spends all current Stress increasing the Tension Level of their personal Arc one Level. This will usually bring on a Scene from that Plot that plays out following the the current Scene directly.') // beyond
);
public static $traumaCards = array(
    array('Type'=>'Intrusive Thoughts', 'Description'=>'Shocks and Traumas can cause a mind to become obsessed with a particular, persistent thought, idea, impulse, or image. These thoughts are experienced as intrusive thoughts, and are often inappropriate to the current situation, and can seem so intrusive as to seem alien. Characters can often become Stressed by these thoughts and agitated when they occur.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates a specific thought, which is given a rating between 1 and 16 (may be randomly rolled) to determine the "severity" or "inappropriateness" of the thought, image or impulse. A 1 would represent a recurring fleeting thought, an 8 might be a single word or short-phrase repeating in their mind, a 16 would represent profoundly disturbing imagery being hallucinated. Intrusive Thoughts move at random through the Psychosocial space, when they are in an Unconscious Space they can be ignored, but upon entering a conscious space (such as Thoughts or any space where their Conscious Self is currently) then the intrusive Thought will immediately occur, causing Stress equal to the "Severity".'),  //ace - ambition
    array('Type'=>'Flashbacks', 'Description'=>'Shocks and Traumas can create vivid, incredibly strong memories in the mind. Later the mind can replay these traumatic experiences as though they are currently happening, often doing so involuntarily as a result of Stress. These experiences can include delusions, hallucinations and paranoia in addition to simple revelries and nightmares.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates an Involuntary Memory, which consists of the events leading to the trauma and the exact emotions (including the Pips and Limit card of the emotional effects) felt at the time. Whenever the Character becomes Overstressed or reminded of this Traumatic event (by similar events) the memories will replay as though the Character was living through them again, this will include all Emotional states once again affecting them with the same intensity.'),  //2 - wraith
    array('Type'=>'Compulsion', 'Description'=>'Shocks and Trauma can make a Character do things, and more importantly want to do things, that they did not want to do before. Compulsions create compulsive behaviours, where even normal behaviours such as exercise, eating, talking, or shopping, become compulsions. Typically the compulsion will be some normal behaviour that is performed to excess, as in binge-eating, or some lack of impulse control, such as over-spending when shopping.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates a compulsion that affects the Character thereafter. This compulsion is given a "Severity" rating between 1 and 16 when created, this may be assigned randomly or based on how dangerous the compulsion is (1 being a mild, or easily overlooked compulsion and a 16 being suicidal or psychotic behaviour). The Compulsion then moves at random around the Character’s Psychosocial space. When in the Unconscious mind the compulsion is ignorable and if performed will relieve Stress equal to the Severity, but when in a conscious part of the Mindscape the Character will be compelled to perform the Compulsion or Gain Stress equal to the "Severity" of the Compulsion'),  //3 - grindstone
    array('Type'=>'Perfectionism', 'Description'=>'Trauma can have strange effects on people, obsession and compulsions can mix and create strange new behaviours and patterns, such as making a person obsessed with being perfect, and achieving perfection. This can create serious issues for a Character, making them unable to perform Tasks unless they can succeed perfectly, leading to procrastination, additional work, micromanagement and unfinished tasks.','Rules'=>'Perfectionist Characters Gain 1 Stress if they roll less than Maximum on any roll, or play non-court cards on Actions. However, if they roll Maximum on any individual die, or play all court-cards in an Action, then they may relieve Stress equal to the number of dice rolled (e.g. a 2d6 relieves 2 when a 12 is rolled) or Pips Reduced.'),  //4 - book
    array('Type'=>'Withdrawal', 'Description'=>'Trauma and Shock can have profound effects on a Character’s social behaviour, often anxiety and Stress from the Trauma will combine in social situations, which can lead to a withdrawal away from all social activities as an avoidance method for more pain. This withdrawal will often lead to less interactions with friends, and abandonning hobbies and activities that might encourage further socialisation. Typically this withdrawal does not cause the Character to abandon friends or allies completely.','Rules'=>'The Trauma can either create a suitable Mild, Taboo or Social Hitch or can permanently delete one Annex that may represent the abandonned hobby or the loss of social skills.'),  //5 - forest
    array('Type'=>'Hope', 'Description'=>'Trauma and Shock can be powerful forces on a Character’s mind and behaviour, but minds can be resilient even in the face of odds that others may call hopeless, and for some individuals hope will remain.', 'Rules'=>'The Trauma alters the Character making them more Hopeful. Whenever they Gain Stress they will also Gain Hopes (Liberty Facet Sway) equal to the Stress. Whenever they Gain Strains they will also Gain 2 Hope, and whenever they Gain Shocks they will Gain 5 Hope.'),  //6 - sun
    array('Type'=>'Escape','Description'=>'Sometimes when Trauma hits, the only thing the Character feels is an urge to escape. This urge can drive them to leave town, change jobs or schools, or even leave their home planet or time.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates an urge to leave a place. The Size of the Location that the Character must move outside of is equal to the total Stress (as Chi). If the Character moves that far they may discard that Stress, so a Character with only 1 Stress must make only a single step, but a Character with 140 Stress would be leaving the continent. Time Travellers can insteaed escape through time, with Extend Duration defining how far they must move in time.'),  //7 - drive
    array('Type'=>'Cultism','Description'=>'Trauma can be spiritual and religious in nature, and can alter beliefs, or at least lead a Character to seek answers beyond the normal orthodoxy of their religion or culture. Trauma causes the Character to question something about their religion, culture, society or politics, and these questions lead them to others with answers (*veracity of answers will vary between cults). Cults vary a lot, some are just reactionary religious sects (Satanists for example), others are led by charismatic narcissists for their own glorification (cults of personality), still others are pervasive terrorist idealogies, you just don’t know what you might find.','Rules'=>'The Trauma leads the Character to question, and seek answers, beyond the cultural confines of their upbringing. This makes them vulnerable to cults who will attempt to recruit them, giving oneself over to the cult allows all Stress to be removed (although cultish living will invariably create new Stress later). This Trauma can create Hitches for the Character as they become members of the cult.') , //8 - cultist
    array('Type'=>'Conversion','Description'=>'Trauma can be political, social, spiritual, or religious in nature as well as psychological or physical, and this can cause a Character to change their opinons about things. When someone has a profound change of opinion about something, like the religion they follow, or political idealogy they subscribe to then we call it a conversion (unless the religion isn’t legitimate somehow when we are in Cultism territory).','Rules'=>'Trauma alters the Character’s opinions about their religion, political beliefs or some other factor. This Trauma immediately relieves Stress equal to the Banes of any Hitches that are converted. E.g. If a Character converts to Christianity following a traumatic possession, then their former Devotion to Pagan gods &times; 12 becomes Devotion: Christian &times; 12 and relieves 12 Stress instantly.'),  //9 - priest
     array('Type'=>'Loner','Description'=>'Trauma can cause a Character to change, become insular and introverted, hateful and anti-social, or they can come to their senses and realise that some people they call friends are not really their friends at all. Whatever the reason, whether betrayal, hazing, secrecy, or mental illness, this Trauma urges a Character to think about who their friends and Allies are very carefully.','Rules'=>'The Character may remove friends and allies from their life (usually without violence, although there may be tears, accusations, and harsh words). Each friend or Ally removed will relieve Stress equal to the Character Type ("unfriending" a Chorus Extra would relieve 5 Stress).'),  //10 - loner
    array('Type'=>'Lessons','Description'=>'Trauma can be a teacher, at least there are often lessons to be learned from the traumatic experience. Trauma can teach a Character a new skill, reveal a hidden talent, or unlock a power. Depending upon the genre, trauma may unlock psychic abilities, unusual perceptions or senses, language, art, memory, musical or mathematical abilities.','Rules'=>'The Trauma allows a Character to purchase with relieved Stress, a new Annex (or just a Proficiency depending on free Slots).'),  //J - teacher
    array('Type'=>'Invention','Description'=>'Trauma can lead to new necessities in a Character’s life, these become the mothers of invention, with the Character creating some new device or technique to deal with the necessity. Sometimes the trauma itself is the necessity, with the mind coming up with some invention as the trauma is occuring, other times the invention may be some safety system to prevent this kind of trauma from occuring in the future.','Rules'=>'The Trauma converts all Stress the Character currently has into Yarn-equivalent Chi that can only be used to create Prototype Descendants.'),  //Q - forge
    array('Type'=>'Notoriety','Description'=>'Trauma can lead to a Character gaining fame within their community or society. This notoriety can be "positive" with celebrity bringing benefts that may offset the trauma somewhat, but notoriety is as often negative, as some folk will try to exploit their knowledge of who the Character is in negative ways.','Rules'=>'The Trauma grants the Character recognition by the masses. This becomes tied to a "Media Impression" similar to a Character’s Impression of them. Most Characters who did not meet the Character before the Trauma will match their Impression of the Character to the media impression, although often those with media exposure themselves will be less quick to adopt the media impression.'),  //K - star
    //hearts
    array('Type'=>'Romance','Description'=>'Trauma can change Characters in wonderful and terrible ways, making them more open, truthful, emotional, or simply causing them to show a more vulnerable side for a while. Vulnerability and emotional-openness can be profoundly attractive, and being openly vulnerable and being cared for by another can also be attractive in return. Although it should be noted that this is rarely the case with professional carers such as Doctors or Nurses, where ethics committees and professional bodies would have something to say about it. Such Romances are often short-lived things, although as with any romance Soul-Stakes are involved.','Rules'=>'The Trauma can alter both Impressions of the Character and the Character’s Impressions of others (increasing the impressions one step for each Stress Relieved) to make them completely trusting of each other, and can create a "Will-They-Won’t-They" Soul-Stakes romance Plot between the two Characters.'),  //ace - lovers
    array('Type'=>'Burn-Out','Description'=>'Trauma can cause a Character to burn-out, whether through fatigue, mental exhaustion, or emotional breakdown. Depression can overwhelm anyone, and will often cause a Character to abandon projects and even relationships. A Burned-out Character should usually be retired from active duty, but may struggle on a shadow of their former selves.','Rules'=>'Trauma causes the Character to Burn-Out, this usually includes relieving all current Stress by creating "Burnt-Out" Hitches that effectively negate the Character’s Annexes. These Hitches can effect only one Annex or all Annexes as the Player, Author, Referee and Yarn-Teller agree.'),  //2 -burnout
    array('Type'=>'Questions','Description'=>'Trauma is bad enough, but sometimes traumas can be compounded by additional problems, such as inquests, political inquiries, insurance problems, as well as disputes over responsibilities and liabities, which all involve a number of very pointed question being asked of the Character.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates Questions for the Character to answer, these questions are usually based on the Character’s Annex Facets, and the Difficulty in answering the Question is usually based on the amount of Stress relieved from the Annex, with the Stress acting as a Chi (Pips) Difficulty usually.'),  //3 - question
    array('Type'=>'Lies','Description'=>'Trauma can bend a Character’s mind, making them have a more loose connection with the truth than they had previously. It may be that the Character is lying to themselves, protecting usually some aspect of their own ego from the truth of what happened during or to cause the trauma, but other times they are pathological lies that serve a different purpose, such as attention-seeking, or deflection. The Character can also become a compulsive liar, who are just more comfortable lying than telling the truth.','Rules'=>'The Trauma alters the Character’s mind, such that whenever they tell a lie they may immediately relieve 1 Stress, some Characters will lie to themselves, others will lie pathologically or compulsively to others.'),  //4 - myth
    array('Type'=>'Humour','Description'=>'Trauma can alter a Character’s sense of humour dramatically, things they previously found funny, may now seem cruel and malicious. Conversely, things the Character previously would have found, trite, sickening, morbid, or boring may now strike them as hilarious. Some Character’s find their sense of humour is destroyed by a trauma, where as others find it to be the ultimate coping mechanism. For others it is a change in styles of humour, moving from whatever they did find funny to puns and wordplay, or sarcasm, satire, prop-comedy, wit, shaggy-dog stories, offensive jokes, sick jokes, crude comedy, physical clowning, sight gags, punchlines, or dad jokes.','Rules'=>'The Trauma alters the Character’s sense of humour in some way. The Relieved Stress from each Annex will change one thing the Character finds funny, either finding something new funny or not liking a style of humour they previously enjoyed. This is usually handled by the Character relieveing 1 point of Stress by laughing or groaning at a Joke that they previously would not or would have found funny, as appropriate.'),  //5 - joke
    array('Type'=>'Nightmares','Description'=>'Traumas always make a deep psychological impact on the Character, and can effectively create damage deep into the brain, these scars express themselves during sleep with night-terrors, corrupted or disturbing dreams and reliving waking memories. Sleep itself can become problematic for the Character, as it is not restful at all, unless they can drink or drug themselves into dreamless sleep.','Rules'=>'Trauma creates Night-terrors, disturbing dreams and nightmares for the Character. The Trauma initially converts all Stress into Nightmare Zones, which a placed in the Character’s Psychosocial Dreamspace. Each Nightmare Zone may have between 1 and 5 Nightmare Points within it, these Nightmare Points are created by the Stress that was placed in them. [t13ne type="table" array="nightmareZones" /]'),  //6 - unicorn
    array('Type'=>'Beast','Description'=>'Trauma can inhibit or push aside the higher mind, revealing the beast underneath. For some the beast is a crazed carnivore, a deadly predator, who has a strong fight response to any stimulus, others revert to fleeing, or freezing in place, we all have base instincts that we repress, sometimes unknowingly. For the beast there is no thought beyond the perception of stimuli and the physical, instinctual, animal response. For some this is a once in a lifetime break, for others it can become a repeatable mental state.','Rules'=>'The conscious mind of a Character is shutdown, or on pause, often this is represented in the Psychosocial Action Space by removing the conscious areas of the mind, instead the Character is reduced to instinctive, animalistic behaviours, they may forage and hunt for food, and often retain instinctual tool use (especially with tools they are familar with holding), empathy and occasionally limited language use, especially at understanding others. Characters in this "mode" cannot Gain Stress from any conscious source, such as Personality Hitches, however they are still effected by emotional effects (perhaps, it could argued, more profoundly without rationalization to inhibit the emotional display) and Psych Attacks (although Psych attacks can only move the Character in the Psychosocial Action Space). The animalistic Character can relieve Stress only by Straining, but can Strain any Facet or Annex Die for 1 Stress.'),  //7 - stag
    array('Type'=>'Gifted','Description'=>'Trauma can profoundly affect the mind, creating new pathways that can open new mental abilities, often abilities unlocked by trauma can be surprising, such as suddenly being able to play a musical instrument, speaking a foreign language, or beoming a lightning calculator. If the Trauma is healed or repaired however the gifted ability is often lost.','Rules'=>'The Trauma immediately creates a Gifted Annex Slot. While the Character has the Trauma they may have an extra Annex Slot. When unlocked all the Character’s current Stress can be relieved by purchasing the Annex and its Proficiencies as though it was Chi.'),  //8 - wizard
    array('Type'=>'Unlucky','Description'=>'Trauma can be the first sign that a Character’s luck has changed for the worst. Once Lady Luck has abandonned a Character she does not return her favour quickly or easily.','Rules'=>'The Trauma relieves all current Stress. However the Stress is replaced by a number Unlucky Failure Levels equal to the total Stress Reduced. While the Character has these Unlucky Failure Levels they can Relieve Stress at any time, converting them into more Unlucky Failure Levels, as long as they add 1d6 Unlucky Failure Levels (or as many as they have left if less) to their last, current or next Action. Once they are out of Unlucky Failure Levels, this Trauma effect is over.'),  //9 lady
    array('Type'=>'Folly','Description'=>'Trauma can cause confusion and disorientation, shutting down former pathways in the brain and making things make less sense for the Character. This is not necessarily a loss of "intelligence", but more an indication that significant parts of that intelligence may now be working illogically or irratically. Where before the Character may have been sensible, even reasonable, this is simply no longer the case. Their confusion may become Quixotic imprudence (tilting at windmills), or Panzaic dullness (skeptical dismissal of the fantastic), or some other delusional reality.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates a confusion or delusion in the mind of the Character, this is often expressed as a Hitch, but also works as follows: The Character can Relieve 1 Stress by <em><strong>either</strong></em> identifying something fantastic and even supernatural as entirely banal (swamp-gas reflecting the light of venus, failed real-estate-developer in a costume, low resolution video of a bird, etc), or by identifying and behaving as is something banal was something fantastic and extraordinary (those are not windmills, they are giants — whirling their swords to attack — we must charge!).'),  //10 - jester
    array('Type'=>'Masking','Description'=>'Trauma can alter Characters dramatically, but it can also cause Characters to pretend it has affected them differently than it actually has. Some people enjoy the attention that comes with trauma, and will exaggerate the effects for more attention. For others, pretending to be someone without the trauma is the game, if they pretend hard enough perhaps the trauma will go away. In some other cases, the Character may assume an unrelated symptom is part of the same thing, which can become incorporated into their diagnosis.','Rules'=>'The Character decides to mask the trauma in some way. Typically the mask will pretend the effects of the trauma were different to the actual effects in some way, often either more or less profound than they actually were. Characters can create an Alt that will act as the "mask" Character, or they can create a "Masking Behaviour" Annex or Descendant to help them hide what is happening (this will relieve Stress to Chi to purchase the Alt, Descendant or Annex).'),  //J - mask
    array('Type'=>'Cloaking','Description'=>'Trauma can sometimes hide other problems. For example, during an accident a Character may snap a limb obviously, they are only concerned about the blinding pain coming from the broken limb. Only once the limb is set does the Character (or the medics treating them) become aware of the muscle damage in their back, or the concussion.','Rules'=>'The Trauma hides a Wound so that it cannot be seen or treated (effectively filling the same Wound Slot with another Wound). The Cloaking Wound is created by relieving Stress, with the Stress relieved equalling the Pips of the Wound, a Limit Card is usually Drawn and Played, that adds Suit and Wound Limit for the Pips. Once this Cloaking Wound has been treated and healed away, the Cloaked Wound will reappear in that Wound Slot. Both the Cloaking Wound and Cloaked Wound occupy the same Wound Slot at once, but the Cloaked Wounds effects and damage are hidden until healed. While a Character has a Cloaking Wound, they may relieve Stress at any time by adding the Pips to their Cloaking Wound, making it potentially Fester, Re-Open or even get worsse as they must Draw a new Limit Card that will replace the old Limit if Higher.'),  //Q - cloak
    array('Type'=>'Medicinal','Description'=>'Trauma can sometimes be medicine, surgery is carefully engineered trauma designed to lessen the damage of other Wounds, but such things can happen randomly. Sometimes a fresh wound will cure, or reveal to medics, a lingering problem allowing treatment to actually cure the underlying problem. It is worth remembering though that despite the narrative trope, a blow to the head will most likely cause a concussion, not cure amnesia.','Rules'=>'The Trauma can affect a Hitch or lingering Wound, using Stress as Chi to directly heal Wounds, and reduce the Banes of Hitches.'),  //K - physician
    //clubs
    array('Type'=>'Punishment','Description'=>'Trauma can sometimes act as a punishment, sometimes this is deliberate, other times the nature of the punishment maybe karmic, poetic justice or irony. Sometimes this punishment seems unjustified, as if randomly assigned (by a card no less), but usually careful examination of the circumstances can reveal some reasonable justification.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates some kind of punishment for the Character, this is often in the form of a Hitch or a lingering Wound affect (Maiming and Crippling Wounds particularly). The Character can Relieve Stress by complaining about the "punishment" they have received, how unjustified it was etc.'),  //ace - court
    array('Type'=>'Fae-Touched','Description'=>'Trauma can create delusions, hallucinations, waking dreams, and strange beliefs. At one time, those who were touched by such madness were considered blessed, or cursed, by the Fae, and many suspected that there was some deeper truth to this madness. There are stil lingering traces of this, with fairies associated with psychedelic mushrooms, dreamstates and nonsense fantasy.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates a "Faery-Delusion", these are powerful delusions that may or may not be actually connected with F&aelig;ry (the other other world of the F&aelig;). If the Character is genuinely seeing Fairy beings around them, or spending the night in F&aelig;ry to return tired to ouur world in the morning, then trying to convey these stories will cause the Character to instead speak nonsense. Otherwise speaking nonsense, pointing out imaginary or hallucinatory beings, or holding one-sided conversations with an imaginary friend, will Relieve 1 Stress.'),  //2 -Eelafin
    array('Type'=>'Sexual','Description'=>'Trauma can affect the base part of the mind, sexual function, fetishes, and attaction can all be significantly altered by Traumas. Characters who are affected by sexual trauma often have profoundly altered sexual tendencies, insecurities and practices. Some shutdown those aspects of themselves, others may seek to claim ownership by revelling in their changed behaviours.','Rules'=>'Trauma can affect a Character’s sexual behaviour, and desires. Often this will take the form of new sexual behaviours, fetishes and can reveal hidden aspects of a Character’s sexuality, other times this may shutdown sexual drives. The Character may Relieve 1 Stress by indulging in (or repressing) these new sexual desires and fetishes. Typically the number of new behaviours created is equal to the total Stress Reduced when the Trauma occurs (all current Stress is Relieved).'),  //3 - serpent
    array('Type'=>'Turbulent','Description'=>'Trauma can make a mind unstable, with the emotions unchecked, hormones and neuro-transmitters sloshing around their brain at heightened levels. Their neurons are too easily stimulated, which can make them easier to emotionally affect, but such emotional states are never long-lived, as the next stimulation will alter that too.','Rules'=>'Trauma reduces the ability of the mind to defend from Emotional Effects. At the time of the Trauma all Current Stress is Relieved and creates a "Turbulent" Pool. This Pool can spend this Stress as Pips / Chi adding to all Emotional Effects the Character is struck by, increasing the chances of being affected. Additionally, the Character may Relieve Stress, moving it into the "Turbulent" Pool, any time their Emotional State changes (Relieving 1 Stress for each Card of the emotional effect).'),  //4 -waters
    array('Type'=>'Defence Mechanism','Description'=>'Trauma can occasionally be helpful, just as surgery is a case of trauma excising some weakness of the body, so too can trauma remove a perceived weakness of the mind. Characters who are used to certain forms of abuse or trauma will develop coping and defence mechanisms, some of which are more effective than others.','Rules'=>'The Trauma teaches the Character a new Defence Mechanism that they may employ in future. [t13ne type="table" array="psychologicalDefences" /]. When the Character uses this preferred psychological Defence mechanism they will Relieve 1 Stress automatically.'),  //5 - shield
    array('Type'=>'Deindividualisation','Description'=>'Trauma can make a Character feel like they are less themselves than before. Such Characters find themselves drawn to share the opinions of others, to do what they do. In extreme cases a Character can experience a complete loss of self, feeling that they have become a gestalt entity with those they are living with, reflecting more the opinons of those around them than any opinion they may have previous had.','Rules'=>'The Trauma instantly Relieves all Current Stress, but adds a new Persona to the Character’s Personality Annex. Typically this is a "Mocker" Persona, but the Yarn-Teller, Referee, Author or Player can instead pick the Persona of any other Character that the Character spends time with. Additionally, a Deindividualised Character will Relieve 1 Stress whenever they can copy the actions or opinons of another Character, regardless of whether they had other opinions previously.'),  //6 - horde
    array('Type'=>'Pay-Off','Description'=>'Traumas can sometimes lead to a pay-off, this could be an insurance policy paying out, or damages from whoever was responsible, but something happens to give the Character a payment of some sort.','Rules'=>'The Trauma immediately Relieves all Stress converting it all into Chi immediately. The Trauma will also pay Chi equal to the Wound the Trauma involves and the Chi cost of any Hitch generated as well.'),  //7 - crystal
    array('Type'=>'Workaholic','Description'=>'Trauma can drive a Character to focus on their work as a coping mechanism. Some people find work a lot less anxiety inducing than the rest of their life, and for them it becomes an easy decision to invest more of their time into their work.','Rules'=>'The Trauma makes a Character reprioritize their life, such that they can now Relieve 1 Stress by focusing on their work over everything else.'),  //8 - scythe
    array('Type'=>'Crown','Description'=>'Shakespere wrote "Uneasy is the head that wears the crown", and this is usually now phrased as "Heavy lies the head that wears the crown". Anxieties compound upon Trauma and can disrupt a Character’s equilibrium and sleep patterns, slowly driving them towards paranoia and insomnia.','Rules'=>'The Trauma restricts a Character getting to sleep, costing them 1d6 hours of racing thoughts before they can sleep at night, however this sleep deprived state allows the Character to Relieve 1 Stress by thinking the worst of a situation or another Character.'),  //9 - crown
    array('Type'=>'Guardian','Description'=>'Trauma can create all sorts of self-protective behaviours in a Character. Some people will create protective guardian imaginary friends, others develop a new psychological defence mechanism, a few others will learn to attack first, to limit their future risks.','Rules'=>'Trauma can create an new Alt, new defence mechanism [t13ne type="table" array="psychologicalDefences" /], and the Character can Relieve 1 Stress if they attack first.'),  //10 - guardian
    array('Type'=>'Tempestuous','Description'=>'Trauma can make a Character unbalanced, so that they can become emotionally tempestuous, as well as prone to outbursts of violence or loud outbursts such as screaming.','Rules'=>'The Trauma makes the Character more emotional, erratic and prone to outbursts. When they initially take the Trauma all current Stress is Relieved instantly, creating a "Tempestuous Temper" Hitch which will interfere with the Character’s ability to control their emotions, perhaps even creating emotions, or instinctual responses. However the Character will be able to Relieve 1 Stress by using violence outbursts, whether physical or verbal, such as screaming, yelling, cursing, ect.'),  //J - tempest
    array('Type'=>'Temptation','Description'=>'Trauma can create all sorts of problems for Characters, and can place them in situations where they discover things about themselves that even they never suspected. Sometimes the trauma can be directly responsible for a fetish, addiction, or mania for something, othertimes it may be a reaction to the trauma that leads a Character "astray". Medical treatments, as well as recreational activities can become addicting, or problematical, temptations come from many sources, and new temptations are all the more tempting.','Rules'=>'The Trauma grants the Character the ability to Relieve 1 Stress by indulging in a temptation, however they can Relieve all current Stress if they indulge in a new temptation. New temptations can, of course, be dangerous as well as tempting, with Stakes ranging from Medium to Paradoxical depending upon the genre and temptation.'),  //Q - inn
    array('Type'=>'Sorcery','Description'=>'Trauma can unlock abilities that the Character had no idea could even exist, let alone that they had access to them. Usually the Trauma will unlock some latent magical, or mutatagenic, power, this is not often a mental or emotional ability, but some physical effect usually. Of couse, genre and setting will greatly effect what "sorcery" can be unlocked by trauma. Of course, in certain genres and settings any useage of "Magic" can appear delusional, and even in fantasy settings some mages are considered crazy for the things they attempt with their magic.','Rules'=>'The Trauma unlocks a Character’s "magical potential", typically this means that one of their Annexes can access "Magic" Boldly (as Chi). They will calculate Difficulty as though using magic (which is often easier). The Character with this Trauma can Relieve 1 Stress by laughing maniacally as they use their magic, regardless of the consequences.'),  //K - fae noble
    //spades
    array('Type'=>'Uncertain','Description'=>'Trauma can push a Character to their breaking point, to the very edge of sanity, or to borderline of the beyond. Some Characters never quite come back after they have been that far, they forever seem to exist in the liminal space at the edge of rational thought, neither fully rational or irrational, and never certain of anything again. To some they may seem to have retreated into a fantasy world, but some others will note that events from the real world are seemlessly integrated into their fantasies, and often this fantasy may offer deeper insights into what is going on than the "real-world" can suppy.','Rules'=>'Trauma pushes a character to the edge of their sanity. Creating a Psychosocial Location (purchased with Relieved Stress acting as Chi) within their mind that may have overlaps or connections to any other point of the Psychosocial mindscape (which will affect the nature of the Location — for example placing it deep in the Dreamscape may make it seem fantastical, connecting it to Supernatural may allow it limited telepathy, even allowing the Character to retreat beyond their own mindscape for safety in another’s mind. The Character can thereafter Relieve 1 Stress instantly by retreating to this Psychosocial Location, or by acting as though they are Uncertain (what is real, what is right, what they shoud do, etc).'),  //ace - threshold
    array('Type'=>'Toxic','Description'=>'Trauma can twist a Character, easily making personality traits and behaviours more toxic. This toxicity will usually express in passive-aggressions, unwarranted criticism of others, snide remarks, sarcastic attitudes, elaborate excuses for their behaviour, seeking to blame others for any failures, manipulating others for their own ends.','Rules'=>'The Trauma instantly Relieves all current Stress, which is used to purchase a "Toxic" Hitch, that will typically interfere with relationships, create bad impressions and hamper the Character socially. The Toxic Character can Relieve 1 Stress by acting toxic somehow to another.'),  //2 -swamp
    array('Type'=>'Lock','Description'=>'Trauma can create locks, with abilities, knowledge and memories being locked away from the conscious mind by the trauma, often as some form of psychological defence mechanism. Sometimes abilities can also be unlocked by traumas, and other times doors, portals and pathways can be unlocked in the Lea or Psychosocial layers of reality.','Rules'=>'The Trauma takes all current Stress and Relieves it converting it to Chi. This Chi is immediately used to lock or unlock something about the Character. For example, any Bulmäs tasting blood for the first time unlocks the Red Carnivore paths, any tasting "dead" meat unlocks the Black Vermis Paths.'),  //3 - key
    array('Type'=>'Tower','Description'=>'Trauma can lead a Character to seeking safe spaces, building panic rooms, buying and installing security systems, and generally developing vigilance against future Traumas.','Rules'=>'The Trauma causes a Character to feel physically unsafe for a majority of their time. It immediately Relieves all current Stress, but creates an "Unsafe" Pool. They may seek to purchase armour, secure Locations and the like, of a value at least equal to the "Unsafe" Pool, as this will reduce the Pool by 1 each time. They may also Relieve 1 Stress gained later by checking every potential entrance and exit is secured.'),  //4 - tower
    array('Type'=>'Runaway','Description'=>'Trauma can make a Character not feel safe in their own home, and many choose to leave. Some will make careful preparations, purchasing a new place, arranging a new job and selling up, others will just abandon their entire life and escape without a plan. Of course, the second types usually end up in a spiralling descent to more Trauma, and worsening situations, but occasionally they will make progress and build a new life for themselves.','Rules'=>'The Trauma creates a desire to escape their home and situation. The Character may Relieve 1 Stress anytime they make any Action that leads towards escape from their current situation (for example, placing your home on the market, notifiying a landlord you are moving out, applying for a job in another country, being interviewed for a job, or riding a shuttle away will all relieve Stress).'),  //5 - sail
    array('Type'=>'Scheduling','Description'=>'Trauma can have profound effects on a Character, altering how they perceive time and sequences of events. It can cause them to become regimented, adhering to a strict time-table for everything in their life, but it can also adjust a schedule, so that a Character becomes aways early or late.','Rules'=>'The Trauma alters a Character’s relationship with time and changes it. The Character may now choose how they wish to Relieve 1 Stress which can be: by always being exactly, strictly, on time, by always being significantly early for anything, or by always being exceptionally late for anything.'),  //6 - clock
    array('Type'=>'Sword','Description'=>'Trauma can make a Character more dangerous, quicker to anger, and more likely to be carrying a deadly weapon.','Rules'=>'The Trauma can Relieve all current Stress, but creates a "Sword" Pool from the Stress. The Character must keep a weapon Descendant with a cost at least equal to the Sword Pool near them at all times, and can Relieve 1 Stress by using this weapon at High Stakes.'),  //7 - sword
    array('Type'=>'Rivalry','Description'=>'Trauma can alter not just who a Character is, but who their friends are. It can also create new Rivalries, with Trauma revealing a comptetive nature in a Character, directed against their former friends. Then again Trauma can also create new Rivalries in other ways, for example, if two Characters suffer the same Trauma, but cope very differently with aspects of the lingering effects, then those Characters may develop a Rivalry.','Rules'=>'The Trauma relieves all current Stress, converting it into Chi that is used to improve a Rival Character or develop a new Rival. The Rivals may both Relieve 1 Stress by demonstrating their superiority over the other in some way (often by winning a quick Opposed Facet Test or Ordeal).'),  //8 - rival
    array('Type'=>'Robotic','Description'=>'Trauma can make a Character seem like a robot in a number of ways. Many victims of Trauma will suppress or numb their emotions, some focus on logic and rationalism, others can settle into a strict regime of work, so that they don’t have time to think about their past traumas, and for a few injuries may have been healed with mechanical or cybernetic parts (for some such as Eusaiveans they may even be converted into a Cyberwraith), dissociation, psychoses, and delusions convince them that they are no longer really human, embracing their idea of robotic behaviour.','Rules'=>'Trauma may cause a Character to become Cybernetic (with associated Hitch(es) created from current Stress relief), or simply to behave in a robotic way. The Character can Relieve 1 Stress by acting robotically or "inhumanly" in any given situation (working mechannically, suppressing or numbing their emotions, speaking in a flat monotone to avoid displaying emotional cues, ignoring social pleasantries, having no discernable sense of humour, acting "robotic", "undead", or "inhuman" in some way, etc).'),//9 - robot
    array('Type'=>'Fierce','Description'=>'Trauma can unlock hidden strengths and courage within a Character, it can be odd to think that a powerful trauma that can make some Characters afraid of everthing around them, can have the opposite effect on some other Character, making them bold and self-assured to the point of fierceness. Fierce Characters are scary not scared, aggressive not defensive, and have either physical or mental strength and willpower.','Rules'=>'The Trauma allows the Character to Relieve 1 Stress by being bold, assertive, fierce (aggresive), or demonstrating strength of will, or physical strength.'),  //10 - lion
    array('Type'=>'Stranger','Description'=>'Trauma can confuse and delude the mind, making a Character who should feel at home, feel like a foreigner, a stranger in a strange land. The Character may suddenly be bothered by their own culture, what was once traditional and reassuring, can become alien and disturbing, or they may feel drawn to explore some other culture, retreating from their own, and the traumas they associate with it.','Rules'=>'The Trauma will often create a Hitch with Relieved Current Stress, that may reflect this oddness, delusion or strangeness that they feel. The Character will Relieve 1 Stress when act as a stranger or outsider to their own culture in someway, questioning or rejecting aspects of a tradition or cultural more.'),  //J - explorer
    array('Type'=>'Vigilance','Description'=>'Trauma can make a Character wary in the future, they become vigilant, or even hyper-vigilant, always watching the shadows around them, always aware of what is happening, they will awaken if a floorboard creaks, and know exactly which stair it was. Their mind is constantly scanning their environment for any threat, no matter how large or small, no matter how unlikely, they are almost impossible to surprise, although they may drop their guard slightly immediately after they have spotted and avoided a potential threat.','Rules'=>'The Trauma makes a Character vigilant, or even hyper-vigilant, this typically adds the Character’s current Stress as Pips to all Actions to do with watching, vigilance or paranoid defensive behaviours (such as never sitting with your back to a door, keeping a gun or knife under your pillow, or sleeping in the hotel bath after arranging the bed to appear occupied) but this does not count as Straining. The Character can Relieve 1 Stress by finding a potential threat in their environment (such as spotting a figure hiding in shadows, or noticing a loose bit of carpet, and not tripping on it.'), //Q -scope
    array('Type'=>'Butcher','Description'=>'Trauma can do odd things to people, making them change their diet, or their behaviour, temperament or even make them hear voices in their head that they can only silence by killing. Sometimes an intense trauma will break a person to their moral core, unleashing a predator, that may appear more monster than person.','Rules'=>'The Trauma Relieves all Current Stress, converting it to Chi and using this to purchase a new Hitch, Alt or Monster Facet (the new Alt can also be a Monster if you like).'), //K- butcher
    array('Type'=>'Worldly','Description'=>'Trauma will sometimes change everything or anything about a Character, and sometimes Trauma will pass without any repercussions, this is one of those times.','Rules'=>'This Trauma instantly Relieves all Stress. This Stress is used as Chi to remove any effects from the Trauma.'), // world
    array('Type'=>'Beyond','Description'=>'Trauma can change a Character in really vital ways, like their vitality, this Trauma kills them.','Rules'=>'The Trauma immediately Relieves all Stress into Chi. Then the Character "dies", releasing all their Sway as a Yarn-burst, and then moves to another layer of reality, or alters their Incarna as required (See Death and Immortality Rules).') // beyond
);

public static $socialAgeCards = array(

    array('Type'=>'Opportunity', 'Description'=>'An Age of Opportunity is occuring. Opportunity can come from a lot of different sources, historical examples include, expansion into uninhabited territories, colonization, access to new or better goods and services, creation of faster trade routes, gold (and other) rushes, technological developments, popular social movements, cultural shifts, and they generally follow the rules of supply and demand.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Opportunity multiple new goods and services will appear, along with a demand for each good and service. All Suppliers will be in competition to fulfil the same demands. For the suppliers the goal is to corner as large a proportion of all demands as possible. Securing all of a demand creates a monopoly, an ideal situation for a supplier, but not for the economy, which will often stagnate. Technologically there is always a demand for a "Better ..." that can break any monopoly.'),  //ace - ambition
    array('Type'=>'Retrospection', 'Description'=>'An Age of Retrospection is occuring. During this age a society dwells upon its past, such times can be both positive and negative for a society. Fashions, for example, often fixate upon some period look, reproducing, or reflecting it in someway, and similar cycles can be seen in popular arts, music, movies and television programming. Even nation states can go through an age of retrospection, with varied results.', 'Rules'=>'An age of retrospection can examine the past truthfully and shortly, without harm. Even celebrating a false (or heavily "edited" or "reframed") version of history can be good for a society, no one wants to be the bad guy in their own history. However, dwelling in the past, trying to recreate past glories, undo progress, or "go back to a simpler time" are all doomed to failure, as they usually always represent that time period unrealistically in the first place, glorifying some aspects while ignoring a host of others. If retrospection continues too long the society stagnates and collapses.'),  //2 - wraith
    array('Type'=>'Endeavour', 'Description'=>'An Age of Endeavour is occuring. During this age a society works towards a common goal, not all members will necessarily be directly working on the goal, but they will support the Endeavour of the age in some way. Examples can include building infrastructure, construction of new buildings, towns or cities (although these are sometimes better handled by an age of expansion), development of some new required technology (such as the clock, space race, or sustainable power generation), survival usually of a diaspora, exodus, or migration. During this age the wealth of the society is tied up in the project and the society may appear poorer as a result.', 'Rules'=>'The society sets some enormous goal and then works towards it, with thousands of individuals contributing Score and Sway to complete an enormous Pact Ordeal, often due to the scale of such projects they require years or even decades of work to achieve their final goal, and along the way many individuals will have to complete smaller, but equally important sub-Ordeals, to actually complete the work.'),  //3 - grindstone
    array('Type'=>'Reason', 'Description'=>'An Age of Reason is occuring. During this age, knowledge and logic are valued, this usually enables a scientific, technological or cultural advance to be made by the society. Such periods usually include a host of discoveries, developments or rediscoveries, that can quickly, and often, lead onto another age.', 'Rules'=>'An age of reason where science, history and knowledge are celebrated and expanded upon, are always revolutionary somehow for a society, but always short-lived turning into another type of age after a few discoveries have been made.'),  //4 - book
    array('Type'=>'Dispersal', 'Description'=>'An Age of Dispersal is occuring. During this age a society sheds members, sometimes due to death and old age, more often they dissolve into other (neighbouring, related or more popular) societies, some few may remain in the original, but it will now be a smaller, more tightly aligned group.', 'Rules'=>'More than half of the members of the society fade away, ceasing their membership, often including former leadership roles. There must be a change of orientation or direction for the group, along with a change of leadership, or this age will end when the social group has completely collapsed.'),  //5 - forest
    array('Type'=>'Enlightenment', 'Description'=>'An Age of Enlightenment is occurring. During this age great discoveries are made, it is an age of exploration, both geographically and culturally. The society looks beyond itself, and seeks betterment by incorporation of ideas it finds there. These ideas may come from the society’s past, a neighbouring culture or group (as during the actual enlightenment), some distant colonised land, or as a result of some out-group within the society (such as mathematicians, scientists, clergy or magicians). A society will often evolve culturally and technologically during this age, and may not resemble itself at all following the age.', 'Rules'=>'Enlightenment is pictured as shining a light upon oneself and one’s culture, but this must usually be done from an exterior position, such as through the window of a foreign or ancient culture. Elightenment can have a profound affect upon a society, changing almost everything about its culture in a revolutionary way.'),  //6 - sun
    array('Type'=>'Vehicles','Description'=>'An Age of Vehicles is occurring. During this age a society gains access to a new method of travel, this opens up new vistas of trade and exploration for the society, granting them additional freedoms and responsibilities. Examples from history include the "Age of Oars", "Age of horse", "Age of Sail", "Age of Steam", "Automobile Age", "Jet Age" and "Space Age". Although technically every new vehicle creates its own age, many are short-lived events for that society, where as others can continue for a very lonng time.', 'Rules'=>'Access to a new vehicle or mode of transport within the society will have dramatic impacts upon that society. Additional freedom of movement, speed of travel, cheapness of trade and so on will positively affect the society, although responsibilities such as rail-road or fleet building can cost a society in the short-term the eventual benefits usually outweigh the costs.'),  //7 - drive
    array('Type'=>'Schism','Description'=>'An Age of Schism is occurring. During this age a society fractures and schisms as the society breaks apart due to internal pressures. During this period ideological or political differences will create internal groups following individual leaders within the society. During the age of Schism the internal sides will compete to control the society as a whole.', 'Rules'=>'During an age of Schism a group will break apart, creating internal factions each with their own leadership, who will compete for actual control.') , //8 - cultist
    array('Type'=>'Belief','Description'=>'An Age of Belief is occurring. During this age the beliefs a society holds are considered more important and true than any evidence that may disprove it. During this age a society will ignore advice, avoid evidence, declare science to be false without evidence, and double down on nonsensical beliefs.', 'Rules'=>'During an age of Belief members of a society will only accept information that supports the belief they have adopted, all other information will be ignored, dismissed or rejected.'),  //9 - priest
     array('Type'=>'Isolation','Description'=>'An Age of Isolation is occuring. During this age a society reduces connections with other societies, this may be an active choice to limit association, or this can be an ostrasization, where they are forced out of contact by an external factor. This insularity within a society will always have a deleterious effect, resulting in stagnation, contraction and occasionally collapse.', 'Rules'=>'Connections to other societies are lost, restricted or limited, usually caused by external factors such as criminal enterprises, larger politics, and geo-politcal events such as wars.'),  //10 - loner
    array('Type'=>'Teacher','Description'=>'An Age of a Teacher is occurring. During this age a teacher will be revealed within the society, this teacher may act as a leader, guiding the society towards some improvement or advancement, or more often they will train the next generation, inspiring rather than leading, sometimes to be a revolutionary force within the society. It should be noted though, that while the teacher has a profound impact, this is not necessarily and age of learning, and may be a rejection or reaction to the actual teachings.', 'Rules'=>'A Character within the society will become a Mentor to either the whole society or to the youth of the society, that will encourage, lead, or inspire improvements, advancements and change in the society.'),  //J - teacher
    array('Type'=>'Industry','Description'=>'An Age of Industry is occurring. During this age a society is working, often maufacturing some item, or providing some service, that is well desired far beyond the society, producing an enormous amount of trade and wealth. Things are obviously positive economically, with close to full employment within the society and a sense that there is more work to do than time or available people-power. Societies and the individuals they are made from get rich during this age, even the poorest members of the society will be well off compared to another society.', 'Rules'=>'The entire society has an economic and industrial boom, often driven by a single product or service that the society may have a monopoly on. Such booms often have a limited duration, after which the society may move to another industry or service, or enter a new age. During Ages Industry the Potency Level of the Craft Facet is often, at least temporarily, increased a level, as some new Tool, procedure or technology is invented that changes the paradigm.'),  //Q - forge
    array('Type'=>'Glory','Description'=>'An Age of Glory is occurring. During this age a society reaches the next level somehow, although often such glories are followed by failures, for the moment everything the society attempts is successful. Ages of Glory are often claimed to be caused by some technological achievement, but there are always multiple foundations for the success in this age. An age of Glory can often cause a society to defeat or even consume their enemies, as kingdoms rise to become empires and colonial powers.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Glory everything the society attempts will be successful (at least until the age is over, when repercussions and consequences may emerge from that initial success). Often Ages of Glory will allow Pacts to alter the Pillar Proficiencies, adding a new Pillar as they also increase the Potency Level of a particular Facet.'),  //K - star
    //hearts
    array('Type'=>'Romance','Description'=>'An Age of Romance is occurring. During this age narratived (often at least one Arc Plot and several Stories) will shape the society, often these narratives include love, attraction and betrayals, usually this narrative is based upon a choice, perhaps a society will be presented with two potential alliances, siding with one will alienate the other, another example is that two sides within society are opposed to each other, within that context members of both sides fall in love. Note that during an age of Romance many narratives may unfold, concurrently and in series.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Romance the entire age is woven by Plots for the society. Embodiments will be chosen exclusively from within the society. An age of romance can tie directly into Mythic Cycles for that universe, although that is not in any way guarranteed.'),  //ace - lovers
    array('Type'=>'Collapse','Description'=>'An Age of Collapse is occurring. During this age the society suffers some setback or blow, members may be lost, people may flee the area and society, another society may grow more popular, this may be a temporary setback, a compacting, or it can represent a complete collapse to nothingness.', 'Rules'=>'During a Collapse a society loses a significant number of members due to some external factor, sometimes dramatic geo-political events such as war, famine, pestilence or plague, other times members simply drift away to find new hobbies, or lands. Major collapses of society can cause Pillar Proficiencies of the Tapestry to fall, lowering the Facet Potency Level as the old ways are forgotten or displaced.'),  //2 -burnout
    array('Type'=>'Inquisition','Description'=>'An Age of Inquisition is occurring. During this age some power arises within the society that calls for some investigation of the society. Often an inquisition is religious or political in nature, rooting out heretics, dissidents, terrorists, or revolutionaries, but scientific and medical inquisitions can also occur. Inquisitions are usually characterised by a loss of individual rights, prejudicial examiners, biased courts and cruel and unusual punishments.', 'Rules'=>'Some faction within the society achieves a position of power and uses it to root out supposed opposition, usually in the form of a witch hunt or inquisition against this supposed opposition. Success in this inquisition can be beneficial for a society (if they have been infiltrated by a foreign power for example), but failure to find supposed opposition while being convinced of its existence will have a negative effect upon the society, paranoia and mistrust can quickly destroy a society from within. A failing inquisition will sometimes create new factions who are opposed to the inquisition which can tear a society apart.'),  //3 - question
    array('Type'=>'Myth','Description'=>'An Age of Myth is occurring. During this age aspects of legend and the world’s Mythic Cycle will shape the society during this age. This can include a shift of tone and genre, adding elements of horror, fantasy, science-fiction and folklore to any other genre. During an Age of Myth fantastical monsters and wizardly magic may appear, in Terminal Thirteen this often includes an F&aelig; incursion, Bulmäs migration, or some spiritual awakening.', 'Rules'=>'During the Age of Myth additional fantasy, horror and mythic tropes may be added to stories, a magical emergence will often occur, and Monsters are often more extreme and obvious. An Age of Myth will often add mythic, magical or monstrous Pillar Proficiencies to the Tapestry, and raise which ever Facet the mythic force draws power from a Potency Level.'),  //4 - myth
    array('Type'=>'Whimsy','Description'=>'An Age of Whimsy is occurring. During this age a society values play, sport, entertainment and escapism over industry or advancement. During an age of whimsy artists, musicians, sportsmen, actors, writers, and similar individuals are seen as social leaders and revolutionaries, and new artforms and styles will emerge during the age. Politics during this age is often more driven by character than by policy, which can lead to popularism and extremist politics arising to end the age.', 'Rules'=>'A period of cultural growth and diversity that creates new artforms, musical genres, styles and fashions. The Age will often end with some reactionary event or social force. During an Age of Whimsy a new Pillar Proficiency will replace one of the current Pillars, as some new art form or style appears, but this often does not involve a change in Facet Potency Level. Cinema replaced Theatre as a Pillar Proficiency in the Tapestry of western civilization about a century ago, but it didn’ increase notably in potency until sound recording and colour film was invented, which created the Golden Age of Holywood.'),  //5 - joke
    array('Type'=>'Liberty','Description'=>'An Age of Liberty is occurring. During this age the society grants freedoms, liberties and rights to members of the society, often there is a general relaxation of rules, as police and militias are stood down, take, or are given a more liberal approach to their roles. An Age of Liberty relaxes societies mores, making society more permissive and experimental as a whole, but this does not always sompletely translate to the most conservative members of the society, who may relax a little, but not to the excesses of the more liberal. An age of Liberty has a lot in common with the ages of crime, decadence, chaos and ostentation, in that it is often (although not always) followed by a collapse of some sort.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Liberty society will be pushed towards being more open-minded, granting members of the society additional rights, privileges and responsibilities, this is usually achieved by more permissive leadership, less conservatism in society in general also helps, as does a free press, media, uncensored communications, art and culture, and a youth-engagement in politics, although there is always a conservative reaction within the Age of Liberty (which can result in the creation of new stories) that often focuses on some singular aspect of the age as a step too far. Age of Liberty can create and alter Pillar Proficiencies of a Tapestry, but often this change will indicate a lowering of some Facet Potency Level, and a loss of a Pillar Proficiency somewhere, in exchange for an increase and new Pillar Proficiency elsewhere.'),  //6 - unicorn
    array('Type'=>'Plague','Description'=>'An Age of Plague is occurring. During this age the society is afflicted by some plague, often an abundance of a particular animal, although plagues can also be bacterial or viral in nature. Plagues devastate societies, mice and locust plagues target foods destroying crops and stores, any plague can spread disease, tainting water supplies, or bringing people in close proximity to dead and living animals.', 'Rules'=>'An animal species explodes in population, such that they appear everywhere, this creates a tremendous negative effect upon the society, as too many animals spread disease and damage property and food stores. Plagues can indicate a shift towards a more natural, overgrown, chaotic, polluted or corrupt world, increasing the Potency of Nature, Quiet, Miasma or Sin, but reducing the potency of Craft, Fury, Phoenix or Virtue, depending upon the nature of the Plague.'),  //7 - stag
    array('Type'=>'Wizardry','Description'=>'An Age of Wizardry is occurring. During this age great masters of some art, craft, magic or technology arise within the society. These wizards can usher in a new technological or artistic age as they alter the whole world around their society trough their great works. Often these wizards are forever remembered as great philosophers, scientists, engineers and artists.', 'Rules'=>'Among the society several Characters are selected as Wizards, these Characters can work seeming magic as they shift the Difficulties of a Test from Banal to Intrepid, onto Bold, Monstrous or even Twisted for all who attempt similar feats following them. Wizard Characters can create new Pillar Proficiencies for the Tapestry increasing the Facets they use in Potency Level.'),  //8 - wizard
    array('Type'=>'Chance','Description'=>'An Age of Chance is occurring. During this age unlikely coincidences and examples of extreme luck dominate the society, there is often an air of gaming, gambling, and an association with underclasses, criminality, and  this creates great unbalances and destabilising forces within a society, as the old fabric may be destroyed as some rich become poor, and some poor become rich randomly. These need not be economic riches, cultural mores and fashions can shift randomly, what was unfashionable and ostracizing before can become cool. An Age of Chance can create charmed individuals who always seem to land on their feet, no matter what, as well as cursed individuals who never catch a break.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Chance all members of a society will receive Chance Success Levels and Chance Failure Levels that are randomly assigned, this number is created by Liberty and Wyrd Annexes each rolling a die roll based on Facet Values from all members of the society. For societies greater than 15,000 members assume a 6d20 rolled Score Reduced for both the Successes and Failures, this gives each member a Score between 6 and 120 or between 2 and 18 Success and Failure Levels each. These Success and Failure Levels are activated by the Referee, Yarn-Teller or Author/Player randomly throughout the Age.'),  //9 lady
    array('Type'=>'Jest','Description'=>'An Age of Jest is occurring. During this age wits, humour and comedy are greatly valued within the society. While they generally do not become leaders themselves, comedians, clowns, jokers and jesters are accorded great fame and often some political power within the society in this age.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Jest Stakes are usually limited to Medium at best, unless a weapon is drawn. However, comedy and humiliation can operate at Higher Stakes (including Soul Stakes) if the comedian wishes to humiliate and harm their target.'),  //10 - jester
    array('Type'=>'Pretence','Description'=>'An Age of Pretence is occurring. During this age the society values lying and pretence more than actual accomplishments. During this age the leaders of the society will also be liars and deceivers, and the society will usually be misled by them, for their own personal goals. The society will treat gossip, stories and anecdotes with equal validity often without checking for evidence. ', 'Rules'=>'During the Age of Pretence clearly showing disbelief will be viewed as rude, insulting and have a negative impression within the society. Appearing to believe something that is probably false will be viewed positively within this society at this time.'),  //J - mask
    array('Type'=>'Secrets','Description'=>'An Age of Secrets is occurring. During this age a society becomes secretive and self-protecting. A society in an age of secrets may make the society into a secret society, with membership never revealed beyond the society, but this is not guarranteed. Secrecy may protect the society from some external threat, or it may be intended to keep some secret, such as a source, technique or technology to maintain a monopoly. Historically the greatest example is probably the silk trade, which caused the nation of China to maintain an age of Secrets, protecting knowledge of the silk worm for around a millenium.', 'Rules'=>'Certain information within or about the society is protected by a veil of secrecy, how far the society will go to keep those secrets will vary with the secret and society, but most will consider killing more acceptable than dying to preserve a secret.'),  //Q - cloak
    array('Type'=>'Recovery','Description'=>'An Age of Recovery is occurring. During this age a society heals and recovers from the wounds of the past, rifts will be mended, and the society will resettle into a new harmony. There may be a few scars and other signs of damage left behind, but most members have put the bad times behind them, whatever they were. During this age economic and cultural recovery will also occur, which may advance the society into a new age.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Recovery a society will recover from whatever harm has previously befallen them. Typically this will mean a period of steady growth in membership, economic, artistic, technological and cultural successes are also possible to recover something previously lost.'),  //K - physician
    //clubs
    array('Type'=>'Law','Description'=>'An Age of Law is occurring. During this age a society will become increasingly law-abiding and litiguous, where as once in a society members may have discussed their differences, or even dueled, now such disputes are settled before a magistrate or judge, often with the aid of numerous legal counsellors, barristers, lawyers, solicitors, clerks and bailiffs all being involved and paid. An Age of Law will usually involve an improvement in law-enforcement for the society, with police or guards being paid more, better trained and equipped, as well as being bolstered in numbers, typically.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Law Characters will attempt to resolve all disputes by legal proceedings, rather than other, less expensive methods. Criminality will always impart a negative impression during this age, even to other criminals.'),  //ace - court
    array('Type'=>'Jumbling','Description'=>'An Age of Jumbling is occurring. During this age the society encounters and merges with another society. This intermingling of societies causes both to grow and approach the other culturally. Societies often gain or swap proficiencies, technologies, artistic styles, words or grammatical peculiarities, as well as creating a new culture during this time.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Jumbling a society blends itself with at least one other, essentially creating a new culture within the society, this new culture may later move to dominate the society, or may later be rejected by the spciety as a whole.'),  //2 -Eelafin
    array('Type'=>'Crime','Description'=>'An Age of Crime is occurring. During this age criminal enterprise is most important for the society, whether created by draconian prohibitive laws, or liberal market forces this society contains a strong criminal underworld. Black markets, drug dealing, thefts, bank robberies, violence and criminals, thieves, and gangsters rule the streets and the headlines, and the police if active at all, are either corrupt, or act as just another gang. In this age it can seem like crime not only pays, but may be the only pay-day. You will find few rich people in this time who do not have criminal contacts and investments.', 'Rules'=>'During the Age of Crime a society tends towards criminality and violence. Even high ranking members of society will have criminal contacts, such as drug-dealers, black marketeers, fences and even assassins.'),  //3 - serpent
    array('Type'=>'Inundation','Description'=>'An Age of Inundation is occurring. During this age pressure builds within society, like water gathering behind a dam, exactly what is the cause or experession of this pressure will vary everytime the age occurs. Usually this pressure pushes Characters together, as a flood will push a community further from the river.', 'Rules'=>'An Age of Inudnation creates a pressure on or within the society, this may be a literal pressure, too many people in too small a Location, or dramatic cliff erosion taking houses from the town, but is more likely a metaphorical pressue, such as the economoic pressures placed on high streets by out of town supermarkets, or the cultural pressure between neighbouring sports teams. This pressure is often expressed through Push Embodiments of the Facets within the society (and beyond) that best represent the sources and expressions of the pressure.'),  //4 -waters
    array('Type'=>'Protection','Description'=>'An Age of Protection is occurring. During this age the society acts to create a safe environment for itself, its members and its allies. Protective societies often include social outreach, charities for the poor and disadvantaged (at least members, sometimes allies), as well as socialised, and sometimes professional, military and health care (usually).', 'Rules'=>'During the Age of Protection the society attempts to protect itself, its members and its allies, often by building defences, obstacles, training guards or police etc.'),  //5 - shield
    array('Type'=>'Congestion','Description'=>'An Age of Congestion is occurring. During this age a society swells in numbers, but not in territory, leading to overpopulation and complications for the society. This can appear similar to Inundation, however there are no external forces at play only internal pressures, which results in different problems and solutions.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Congestion Characters competition for space is greater, this increases Stress for all members of the society based on the difference in the society Group Size versus the Location they occupy as Chi. E.g. a couple of Thousand people (26) require the space of a city block (26) to live comfortably, if they all try to live in a single large public building like a Museum (14) this would create 12 Stress each day for every member of the society. This Stress will often force the society to expand their territory (although this can lead to an Age of Inundation as they encounter exterior forces).'),  //6 - horde
    array('Type'=>'Ostentation','Description'=>'An Age of Ostentation is occurring. During this age a society becomes obsessed with demonstrations of wealth, power, bravado, pagentry and general excess. The society is rich, but is not humble, spectacles, splendor and splurges are the fashion of the day, as the society swaggers around flaunting its own magnificence. Usually this age is as a result of previous economic success, with little done during the age to prepare for future hard times, the fashionable baubles purchased at great expense now, will be worth nothing when the collapse comes.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Ostentation a society fritters away the wealth it has previously created on fashions, parades, excessive and often questionable celebrations, rather than saving that wealth for leaner times, or reinvesting it to secure the future (although some within the society may do this and be rewarded later for their forward thinking).'),  //7 - crystal
    array('Type'=>'Accumulation','Description'=>'An Age of Accumulation is occurring. During this age a society reaps the rewards of their hard work and planning. This is a time of production, resource gathering, and manufacturing success and generates wealth for the society, individual members get richer, financially and culturally and society improves as a result. The age cultivates new cultural, artistic, manufacturing, management, and educational trends within the society, bringing in new knowledge, resources, techniques, styles and sciences from other societies, which benefit the society greatly moving forwards. This accumulation of knowledge, wealth and power leads to firther innovations and gains that can be made before the age ends.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Accumulation a society and the individual members make Gains, often of wealth, resources, technologies, knowledge and fashions that lead to further accumulations.'),  //8 - scythe
    array('Type'=>'Governance','Description'=>'An Age of Governance is occurring. During this age a society is lead by a powerful leader, this leader may be a benign dictator, a progressive emperor, a democratically-elected successor, a regressive oppressor, a tyrannical despot, or an unfeeling bureaucrat, amongst many other things. Regardless of their way of attaining power and leadership, they are truly in charge of the society, they may be a pinickity micromanager or a sweeping generalizer, but their leadership will have a profound effect (either positive or negative) upon the society.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Governance a leader will arise from within the society that is accepted and followed without question by most of the society. Depending upon the nature of this leader the society may be dramatically positively or negatively effected by them.'),  //9 - crown
    array('Type'=>'Surveillance','Description'=>'An Age of Surveillance is occurring. During this age a society watches itself, perhaps by introducing journalism, watchmen, police officers, video surveillance cameras, or internet tracking systems. Typically this watching simultaneously makes a society safer and more paranoid, until you reach a situation where you have nothing to fear, but are constantly afraid.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Surveillance a society increases both social paranoia and physical security, there will be less crime (possibly even zero crime), but this is replaced with increased paranoia and Stress for anyone who lives in the society. Typically all members of society gain Stress whenever they see signs of the surveillence (police, security guards, cameras, cell towers, etc), with Traumas often causing paranoid behaviour .'),  //10 - guardian
    array('Type'=>'Chaos','Description'=>'An Age of Chaos is occurring. During this age a society experiences upheavals, disturbances, tumults and uproar from within. Normal functioning within the society, such as trade, travel, leadership and communications are disrupted, usually this is not a complete disruption, but a limited period of disruption. Historically ages of chaos can include natural disasters, political upheavals, invasions, wars and similar historical events.', 'Rules'=>'During the age of Chaos, everything changes, trade, communications and travel beyond and within the society is interrupted or confused somehow. Life within the society is more stressful and at higher Stakes than normal, during the age of Chaos.'),  //J - tempest
    array('Type'=>'Decadence','Description'=>'An Age of Decadence is occurring. During this age society revels in immorality, iniquity, sinfulness and wrongdoing, rather than just the excesses of wealth. Although the wealthy will display impropriety too, extravagant debaucheries that rival those of an age of ostentation, for the underclasses of society there is just as much excess in some ways, but it often involves stronger or at least cheaper booze.', 'Rules'=>'During the Age of Decadence most members of society will develop at least one additional Hitch that reflects the dark hobbies they are developing during the age.'),  //Q - inn
    array('Type'=>'Magic','Description'=>'An Age of Magic is occurring. During this age there is within a society some belief in magic. This is not necessarily a Mythic age that actually contains magic, although that can occur too, but more a rejection of materialistic mainstream knowledge, particuarly sciences. Magical thinking and beliefs may include fantastical or just misapplied mystical or scientific concepts, that can have positive and negative effects upon the society. Shared rituals, experiences and beliefs can draw a community closer together, but lead to irrational decision-making, social stagnation, and extremism.', 'Rules'=>'Magical thinking and beliefs are accepted within the society, often causing a rejection of materialistic scientific beliefs and counter-evidence. Often accompanied by a profound change in the society, often with a shift towards more popularist and extremist politics.'),  //K - fae noble
    //spades
    array('Type'=>'Emergence','Description'=>'An Age of Emergence is occurring. During this age society stands upon the brink of a great sea-change in thinking, some paradigm shift is underway, and after the age has finished some aspect of society will be forever altered. The whole society will be affected and altered by this shift in perspective, historically these revolutionary ideas have caused huge changes in culture and the path of history, the industrial revolution changed how the world worked, the assembly line altered businesses and factories forever, the internet altered communications and information retrieval completely.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Emergence some new paradigm, theory or technology sweeps the world, changing all societies. Societies that fail to adapt to the Emerging new world usually swiftly collapse, hoever those that can exploit some new niche of the new world quickly thrive.'),  //ace - threshold
    array('Type'=>'Corruption','Description'=>'An Age of Corruption is occurring. During this age society begins to break down, individual members of the society behave in their own self-interest, rather than the interest of their society. Corruption, extortion, exploitation, fraud, profiteering, racketeering, malfeasence and nepotism are the order of the day, often with a hint of social injustice and base criminality. A corrupt society does not serve its membership and they will often form new societies, abandonning their old, where they cannot fix the society’s ills.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Corruption most members turn aside from the society, whether to exploit the other members, make a quick buck, or to excape the corruption within the society. This allows exploitation narratives and corruption stories to Embody within the society. Allowing an age of corruption to continue unchecked always has a negative effect upon the society, costing them membership to other nearby, and less corrupt societies, and often leading to a complete collapse.'),  //2 -swamp
    array('Type'=>'Crux','Description'=>'An Age of Crux is occurring. During this age a society must make an important choice or decision, that will later appear as a tipping point in history (a crux event). Typically during this age a society will choose between one action and another (whether to side with neighbour A or neighbour B during the war), although action and inaction (whether to invade or not) choices also occur. While the society as a whole may feel this crux age upon them, it is often the choice of a single individual that defines and ends the age, although no decision is made in a total vacuum and the beliefs of the society around the individual will have a powerful part of that decision-making process.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Crux a single crucial decision (often important for a variety of reasons, most of which will not be obvious until after it is made) affects a whole of society, often an individual will make the crucial decision (usually a leader within the society), but decisions can be voted upon by the whole, or a section, of a society too. The decision that must be made during an Age of Crux is usually a Crux Event or Causal Nexus Event (see Events for details) with all members of the Society contributing Sway to creating and enforcing the event, adding Edges and Glows, etc.'),  //3 - key
    array('Type'=>'Expansion','Description'=>'An Age of Expansion is occurring. During this age a society will seek out new territories and locations, and construct and build upon this new land they have acquired. Societies in this age will often build an impressive building or buildings that will become historically significant with time, such as churches, cathedrals, tithe barns, exchanges and official market buildings, banks, palaces, henges, castles, citadels, town walls, town halls, public baths, court buildings, etc.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Expansion a society and the individual members will undertake various Ordeals to capture, colonise, explore, find, gain, purchase or rent a new location, and convert that location to their purposes, often by constructing infrastructure and buildings in the new Location. Such a society-wide Ordeal is similar to an Age of Endeavour, where the society works for a common goal, in this case the common goal is less common to all members of the society, but the society will benefit from the expansion as a whole.'),  //4 - tower
    array('Type'=>'Dependency','Description'=>'An Age of Dependency is occurring. During this age a society hitches their wagon to another. Sometimes this is a deliberate action by the rulers of the society, to ally with a more powerful society, other times it comes as a result of an invasion or similar geo-political crisis. During the age the society is dependent upon the "root" society for something, often this is a trade agreement, or military self-defence pact with a more powerful partner. Dependence on others can cause friction within a society, especially if this comes after past glories, and the society may feel they are not well enough respected by other allies during this dependence (although often this is simply projection, or rose-tinted nostalgia making some members of the society feel weak compared to their previous position). Typically an age of dependence ends with a breaking away, an indepence revolution, internal collapse, merging into the "root" society, or by politically or technologically manoeuvring into a more dominant position.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Dependency a society is dependent upon another usually larger society, smaller societies may spend the vast majority of their time dependent upon the national or (inter-)planetary society above them. Villages are often associated with towns, towns with counties, counties with states, provinces or principalities, and those with countries, countries with unions and empires etc. Typically a dependent society pays Sway into the root society and the root society returns it as though it were one level higher, but this it is still paid back in the same Sway (e.g. Paying in Chi returns Chi equal to the Value of the Boon).'),  //5 - sail
    array('Type'=>'Urgency','Description'=>'An Age of Urgency is occurring. During this age a society seems to lose patience, everything becomes hurried, with members pressured by society to be swift or even hasty. This urgency throughout society can appear in the individual as boldness, excitement, enthusiasm, fervor, insistence, persistence, desperation, uneasiness, frustration, weariness or hesitency. Sometimes an Age of Urgency is brought on by a need to complete some endeavour or great work quickly, but more often it is a general acceleration of life creating a lack of patience in society. Human progress can largely be tied to the speed of travel and communications that we have achieved.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Urgency all members of a society will gain Stress equal to how long their task will take as an Extend Duration as Yarn (e.g. any task that takes longer than a second will add at least 1 Stress, longer than a moment, but less than two hours will add 2 Stress. Taking on a year or two year long task will add 10 Stress, etc.'),  //6 - clock
    array('Type'=>'War','Description'=>'An Age of War is occurring. During this age a society engages in warfare with another society. Wars come in various types, from the chaotic and bloody, firey mess that is total war, to the relative paranoid quiet of a cold war, or anything in between. All wars contain battles, which are always bloody wastes of lives for both societies, although during cold wars often proxy societies will sacrifice the most, fighting direct, but proxy battles for their cold war allies.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of War a society is engaged in armed (and often armoured) comabt against at least one other society. Wars are complex strategic Ordeals that rely on logistics, intelligence, equipment ease of maintenance, long-term morale and discipline more than actual battlefield prowess.'),  //7 - sword
    array('Type'=>'Rivalry','Description'=>'An Age of Rivalry is occuring. During this age a society develops a profound rivalry with another society, often a neighbour and ally. This rivalry is usually expressed within some sport or competition, although this rivalry may in time develop into a more aggressive and violent situation, it rarely becomes a war. In fact, such rivalries are more commonly a result of a changing geo-political landscape that creates allies of former enemies, this ancient enmity becomes the basis for bitter rivalry in sports, economics, art or some other field.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Rivalry a society will select a rival society from its current allies, often a previous enemy, and compete against them scoring small vitories and loses against the rival society. This rivalry will often cause a growth of both societies as they repeatedly compete and improve.'),  //8 - rival
    array('Type'=>'Drudgery','Description'=>'An Age of Drudgery is occurring. During this age a society becomes almost robotic, it is in many ways a zombie society, dead already, but still going through the motions. A society in this state may wake up, revitalise and move formward, but then again it does require someone within the membership realising what is happening and changing something before a complete collapse occurs as some new society offers a better way of life to its members.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Drudgery a society appears to continue their last age, although not to the same result. The society may be blindly producing outdated technology, they may be using a traditional manufacturing method that is no longer competitive, may be fighting an enemy that no longer strictly speaking exists, or they may be following some ancient contract or programming that is long out of date in some other way.'),//9 - robot
    array('Type'=>'Predation','Description'=>'An Age of Predation is occurring. During this age a society draws closer together, either as they prey upon a weaker society, or as they are preyed upon by a larger society. Typically this predation is in the form of exploitation, manipulation and abuse, whether through invasion, theft, warfare or more nefarious means such as trade agreements, enslavement, post-war reparations, aid foundations, international politics, or unchecked commercial practices. Usually the weaker, prey society is "consumed" by the predatory society, who will gain the members (sometimes as prisoners, slaves or as part of a brain-drain). There is some overlap here with Jumbling Ages, but one society is always clearly dominant in an age pf Predation.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Predation the society preys upon and consumes another, usually smaller or less technological society. Members of the smaller predated society may be able to move into the predatory society and those able to move will often do so. Sometimes a prey society may manage to survive, or at least preserve some of their original culture within the new society.'),  //10 - lion
    array('Type'=>'Exploration','Description'=>'An Age of Exploration is occurring. During this age a society explores beyond its borders, seeking unsettled lands that they can add to their own territory. A society often becomes obsessed with the latest exploratory missions, and the discoveries they have found, with new plants, animals, feathers or cultural artifacts. Settlement or colonization of the new land is usually the result of this age. ', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Exploration a society encounters a new territory that they must explore, uninhabited territories may provide new animals, minerals or plants. Inhabited territories will expose the society to a new external (most often ancient or dead) culture, which captures the public imagination for a while.'),  //J - explorer
    array('Type'=>'Inspection','Description'=>'An Age of Inspection is occurring. During this age a society performs an inspection, sometimes this is a retrospective, examining the past, but it is more often introspective, where a society looks within itself. The exact reasons for this can be due to an political, judicial or scientific inquiry that catches the public attention, an artistic, journalistic, political, or social movement, or due to a new broom at the top, sweeping away corruption and criminality. Depending upon what is found and how the society responds to this knowledge can profoundly effect whether this age will be perceived later in a positive or negative light.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Inspection some society wide inquiry or inspection takes place, often this becomes an inspection of the society itself. With similar Questions (defined often by the society’s highest Facet) being asked throughout the society.'), //Q -scope
    array('Type'=>'Feasting','Description'=>'An Age of Feasting is occurring. During this age a society has reasons to celebrate and is often quite rich, but food rather than riches is how society demonstrates those riches. Vast banquets, lavish meals, bountiful harvests, and fat farm animals are the order of the age. Quite what the society is celebrating will depend upon the previous age. Although the age of feasting is a celebration of some sort, it is also a bloody period, death and carrion are all around, flies and rats swarm the back alleys and sickness is never more than a few neighbours away.', 'Rules'=>'During the Age of Feasting a society celebrates the last age or its end, the society is food rich due to good harvests or strong trade. All members of society will be well fed, and healthy, at least at the start of the age. Depending how long the situation remains stable, with trade good, harvests rich and animal stocks well maintained, eventually most members of society will be over-fed, and become quite unhealthy, sickness will inevitably sweep through the society, if famine, drought or trade disruption does not end the situation ealier.'), //K- butcher
    array('Type'=>'Completion','Description'=>'An Age of Completion is occurring. During this age a society riches the end of their story. Typically the society accomplishes some great task, raising a monument for all the ages, crossing some "impassable" barrier such as sailing first across an ocean, conquering some ancient empire and in this great accomplishment, the society then seems to vanish from history. Whatever happened to this society history will not record it, although often that just means that the society changes name, or breaks into a number of smaller societies, occasionally this society collapses, its task complete, the goal accomplished, the society loses cohesion, and the members simply fade away, joining neighbouring societies, or creating a new one.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Completion a society completes some great task, and then collapses, this collapse may be total, partial, or simply a revolution within the society or a change of name. However the story of this society is over.'), // world
    array('Type'=>'Incursion','Description'=>'An Age of Incursion is occurring. During this age a society is infiltrated from beyond, usually this will be simply some foreign power, but in some genres this may be a cross-temporal / hyper-geometric / inter-dimensional / extraterrestrial / ultraterrestrial / supernatural / spiritual / divine / demonic or Increated incursion. The Incursion can be an expedition, infiltration, intrusion, raid, abduction, invasion, usurpation, or just a vacation.', 'Rules'=>'During an Age of Incursion some force from beyond, either the society, nature or even the genre, appears within the society. This incursion can be for any purpose, but represents some exterior unknowable force. When in doubt use any crazy idea, you can always say it was an Increated that nightmare fueled off a nearby insane person later, if necessaary. Incursions can bring changes to not just the society, but the nature of reality itself, as time-travellers, gods or sleeping dragons awaken and emerge into the society.') // beyond

);

